hpIpfEvtDetailStr.name: hpIpfEvtDetailStr
hpIpfEvtDetailStr.description: This string provides a detailed description of the Event along with variable information.

hpevtBadOsInitChecksum.name: hpevtBadOsInitChecksum
hpevtBadOsInitChecksum.description: The OS has registered an OS_INIT vector, but is has not passed the checksum

hpevtBadOsMcaChecksum.name: hpevtBadOsMcaChecksum
hpevtBadOsMcaChecksum.description: The OS has registered an OS_MCA vector, but it has not passed the checksum

hpevtBootBmcFailed.name: hpevtBootBmcFailed
hpevtBootBmcFailed.description: The BMC has failed testing and has been disabled.

hpevtBootCellMonSelFailure.name: hpevtBootCellMonSelFailure
hpevtBootCellMonSelFailure.description: Monarch selection has failed. Data: 0x11 = Calibration Failure 0x22 = Select Code Failure

hpevtBootCellVirtualizeEfiFailure.name: hpevtBootCellVirtualizeEfiFailure
hpevtBootCellVirtualizeEfiFailure.description: SFW attempted to virtualize EFI and failed

hpevtBootCellVirtualizePalFailure.name: hpevtBootCellVirtualizePalFailure
hpevtBootCellVirtualizePalFailure.description: SFW was unable to virtualize PAL

hpevtBootCellVirtualizeSalFailure.name: hpevtBootCellVirtualizeSalFailure
hpevtBootCellVirtualizeSalFailure.description: SFW was unable to virtualize SAL

hpevtBootCellVirtualizeSalprocFailure.name: hpevtBootCellVirtualizeSalprocFailure
hpevtBootCellVirtualizeSalprocFailure.description: SFW was unable to virtualize SALPROC

hpevtBootCpuConfigFail.name: hpevtBootCpuConfigFail
hpevtBootCpuConfigFail.description: SFW has failed initializing the CPU Struct. Data: Physical location of CPU that produced failure

hpevtBootCpuEarlyConfigFail.name: hpevtBootCpuEarlyConfigFail
hpevtBootCpuEarlyConfigFail.description: A CPU has failed early config.

hpevtBootCpuEarlyTestFail.name: hpevtBootCpuEarlyTestFail
hpevtBootCpuEarlyTestFail.description: A CPU has failed early self test. Data: PAL Test State.

hpevtBootCpuFailed.name: hpevtBootCpuFailed
hpevtBootCpuFailed.description: SFW has detected that a CPU has failed. Data: The Physical Location of the CPU that failed

hpevtBootCpuLateTestFail.name: hpevtBootCpuLateTestFail
hpevtBootCpuLateTestFail.description: SFW has determined a CPU or Memory has failed late test. This could be related to a CPU error or a Correctable Single Bit Memory error. Data: Physical location of CPU See Cause/Action.

hpevtBootCpuLateTestInsufficientMem.name: hpevtBootCpuLateTestInsufficientMem
hpevtBootCpuLateTestInsufficientMem.description: The CPU late test has failed because of insufficient memory

hpevtBootEfiAllocateError.name: hpevtBootEfiAllocateError
hpevtBootEfiAllocateError.description: Could not allocate memory for EFI image

hpevtBootEfiNvmFail.name: hpevtBootEfiNvmFail
hpevtBootEfiNvmFail.description: EFI NVM has failed testing. The cell or system will now halt.

hpevtBootExtIntNestLimitedExceeded.name: hpevtBootExtIntNestLimitedExceeded
hpevtBootExtIntNestLimitedExceeded.description: The IVT interrupting nesting depth has been exceeded. This processor will be halted. Data: Number of the offending vector.

hpevtBootExtIntNotServiced.name: hpevtBootExtIntNotServiced
hpevtBootExtIntNotServiced.description: An external interrupt has been requested and not serviced. Data: Number of the vector

hpevtBootExtIntTaken.name: hpevtBootExtIntTaken
hpevtBootExtIntTaken.description: An external interrupt has been taken. Data: Number of the vector taken.

hpevtBootFplFailed.name: hpevtBootFplFailed
hpevtBootFplFailed.description: Access to the FPL has failed.

hpevtBootGetPsrFailure.name: hpevtBootGetPsrFailure
hpevtBootGetPsrFailure.description: SFW was unable to read the CPU PSR. Data: Physical location of CPU

hpevtBootHaltCell.name: hpevtBootHaltCell
hpevtBootHaltCell.description: SFW has halted the cell or system

hpevtBootIncompatiblePal.name: hpevtBootIncompatiblePal
hpevtBootIncompatiblePal.description: SFW has determined that PAL is not compatible with the current processors.

hpevtBootIncompatibleSlave.name: hpevtBootIncompatibleSlave
hpevtBootIncompatibleSlave.description: SFW has determined that a slave processor is incompatible with the monarch. Data: Physical location of the incompatible processor.

hpevtBootIntrptClearFailure.name: hpevtBootIntrptClearFailure
hpevtBootIntrptClearFailure.description: Interrupt clear failed during cell config

hpevtBootIpmiEventFailed.name: hpevtBootIpmiEventFailed
hpevtBootIpmiEventFailed.description: SFW has determined that an IPMI event failed.

hpevtBootLostContextInt.name: hpevtBootLostContextInt
hpevtBootLostContextInt.description: Interrupt context was lost. Data: interrupt number.

hpevtBootMinStateRegError.name: hpevtBootMinStateRegError
hpevtBootMinStateRegError.description: Registering of the processor min state save area with PAL has failed.

hpevtBootMonarchTimeout.name: hpevtBootMonarchTimeout
hpevtBootMonarchTimeout.description: SFW has determined the monarch has timed out. SFW is deconfiguring the CPU. Data: Physical Location of CPU

hpevtBootNoPalBInFit.name: hpevtBootNoPalBInFit
hpevtBootNoPalBInFit.description: A PAL_B FIT error has occurred

hpevtBootNoSalBInFit.name: hpevtBootNoSalBInFit
hpevtBootNoSalBInFit.description: A SAL_B FIT error has occurred

hpevtBootNvmFail.name: hpevtBootNvmFail
hpevtBootNvmFail.description: NVM has failed test. The system will halt

hpevtBootOutOfRangeVector.name: hpevtBootOutOfRangeVector
hpevtBootOutOfRangeVector.description: A interrupt vector has been requested out of the acceptable range. Data: Vector Number.

hpevtBootPalCopyInfoError.name: hpevtBootPalCopyInfoError
hpevtBootPalCopyInfoError.description: The PAL Copy Info call has failed.

hpevtBootPalProcFailure.name: hpevtBootPalProcFailure
hpevtBootPalProcFailure.description: A PAL Proc has failed. This will halt the processor. Data: Physical Location of CPU

hpevtBootPlatConsoleDevFailed.name: hpevtBootPlatConsoleDevFailed
hpevtBootPlatConsoleDevFailed.description: A console device has failed. Data: Physical Addr of device that failed.

hpevtBootPlatIntfcDevFailed.name: hpevtBootPlatIntfcDevFailed
hpevtBootPlatIntfcDevFailed.description: A console device has failed. Data: Physical Addr of device that failed.

hpevtBootPlatScrBad.name: hpevtBootPlatScrBad
hpevtBootPlatScrBad.description: Platform Scratch RAM has failed the test.

hpevtBootRendezFailure.name: hpevtBootRendezFailure
hpevtBootRendezFailure.description: A CPU has failed to enter rendezvous. Data: Local CPU Number

hpevtBootSalExtractError.name: hpevtBootSalExtractError
hpevtBootSalExtractError.description: SFW could not extract SAL_B from the ROM

hpevtBootScrFail.name: hpevtBootScrFail
hpevtBootScrFail.description: Platform Scratch RAM has failed test.

hpevtBootSlaveNoFinalWakeupVector.name: hpevtBootSlaveNoFinalWakeupVector
hpevtBootSlaveNoFinalWakeupVector.description: No wakeup vector registered for processor Data: Physical location of CPU

hpevtBootSlaveRendezHandlerFail.name: hpevtBootSlaveRendezHandlerFail
hpevtBootSlaveRendezHandlerFail.description: Slave Rendezvous handler has failed. Data: Physical Location of CPU

hpevtBootSmbiosBuildError.name: hpevtBootSmbiosBuildError
hpevtBootSmbiosBuildError.description: SFW failed to build the SMBIOS tables

hpevtBootTrapNestLimitedExceeded.name: hpevtBootTrapNestLimitedExceeded
hpevtBootTrapNestLimitedExceeded.description: The trap nesting limit has been exceeded. Data: Vector Number

hpevtBootTrapNotServiced.name: hpevtBootTrapNotServiced
hpevtBootTrapNotServiced.description: A trap has been requested and not serviced. Data: Vector Number

hpevtBootTrapTaken.name: hpevtBootTrapTaken
hpevtBootTrapTaken.description: A trap has been taken. Data: Number of the vector taken.

hpevtBootUnclearedInt.name: hpevtBootUnclearedInt
hpevtBootUnclearedInt.description: At least one interrupt was not cleared. Data: The highest pending interrupt number

hpevtBootUnexpectedExtIntPostRedirTable.name: hpevtBootUnexpectedExtIntPostRedirTable
hpevtBootUnexpectedExtIntPostRedirTable.description: An unexpected external interrupt has occurred. Data: External Interrupt Number

hpevtBootUnexpectedIntPreRedirTable.name: hpevtBootUnexpectedIntPreRedirTable
hpevtBootUnexpectedIntPreRedirTable.description: An interrupt has occurred before setting up the Interrupt Vector Table. Data: Interrupt Number

hpevtBootUnexpectedMca.name: hpevtBootUnexpectedMca
hpevtBootUnexpectedMca.description: An unexpected MCA has occurred before MCAs are unmasked. Data: Local CPU Number.

hpevtBootUnexpectedTrapPostRedirTable.name: hpevtBootUnexpectedTrapPostRedirTable
hpevtBootUnexpectedTrapPostRedirTable.description: An unexpected trap has occurred. The trap number is either invalid or the requested trap has not been registered. Data: Trap Number

hpevtBootUnknownFailure.name: hpevtBootUnknownFailure
hpevtBootUnknownFailure.description: SFW has detected an unknown error.

hpevtErrorsPalFailure.name: hpevtErrorsPalFailure
hpevtErrorsPalFailure.description: SFW has detected a PAL Failure

hpevtExpMcNotRegistered.name: hpevtExpMcNotRegistered
hpevtExpMcNotRegistered.description: Expected Machine Check Vector not registered

hpevtInitInitiated.name: hpevtInitInitiated
hpevtInitInitiated.description: This is the equivalent of a TOC event in the PA RISC Architecture. On IPF systems, this event is called an INIT. This event can be triggered by the 'tc' command from the MP, or from the button labeled 'TOC' :wor 'Transfer of Control' on the Management card or bezel of the system. There are also other causes of an INIT generated by software. Data: Local CPU Number

hpevtIoCheckLbaMissingErr.name: hpevtIoCheckLbaMissingErr
hpevtIoCheckLbaMissingErr.description: An I/O host bridge is missing. Firmware will continue boot and display the following EFI warning, 'Unexpected hardware I/O configuration.' Data Field: Physical location of the missing I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoCheckNumSlotsErr.name: hpevtIoCheckNumSlotsErr
hpevtIoCheckNumSlotsErr.description: Firmware detected an unexpected number of I/O slots connected to an I/O host bridge. Firmware display the following EFI warning message, 'Unexpected hardware I/O configuration.' Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoCheckRopeWidthErr.name: hpevtIoCheckRopeWidthErr
hpevtIoCheckRopeWidthErr.description: Firmware found an I/O controller rope of unexpected width. Firmware will configure the I/O host bridge connected to the rope and display the following EFI warning message, 'Unexpected hardware I/O configuration.' Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge connected to the rope.

hpevtIoCheckXtraLbaFoundErr.name: hpevtIoCheckXtraLbaFoundErr
hpevtIoCheckXtraLbaFoundErr.description: Firmware found an unexpected I/O host bridge. Firmware will configure the I/O host bridge and display the following EFI warning message, 'Unexpected hardware I/O configuration.' Data Field: Physical location of the unexpected I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoDllError.name: hpevtIoDllError
hpevtIoDllError.description: An I/O host bridge's bus frequency DLL circuit failed. Firmware will deconfigure the failed I/O host bridge and display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoHotPlugCtrlFailed.name: hpevtIoHotPlugCtrlFailed
hpevtIoHotPlugCtrlFailed.description: An I/O host bridge's hot-plug controller has failed. Firmware will deconfigure the I/O host bridge and display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoInvalidRopeBundle.name: hpevtIoInvalidRopeBundle
hpevtIoInvalidRopeBundle.description: Firmware attempts to configure an I/O controller rope to an unsupported width. Firmware will deconfigure any I/O host bridge connected to the rope. Data Field: Physical location of the failed rope.

hpevtIoLbaClearErrFailed.name: hpevtIoLbaClearErrFailed
hpevtIoLbaClearErrFailed.description: During I/O host bridge configuration, firmware found a persistent error condition. Firmware will deconfigure the I/O host bridge and display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoLbaResetError.name: hpevtIoLbaResetError
hpevtIoLbaResetError.description: An I/O host bridge is inaccessible because an I/O controller rope reset failed to complete. Firmware will deconfigure the I/O host bridge and display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoNotEnoughPowerError.name: hpevtIoNotEnoughPowerError
hpevtIoNotEnoughPowerError.description: There is insufficient power. Firmware will not power on a hot-plug I/O slot. In addition, firmware will display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Date Field: Physical location of the I/O slot.

hpevtIoPciMappingFailed.name: hpevtIoPciMappingFailed
hpevtIoPciMappingFailed.description: Firmware encountered an unexpected error while attempting to configure an I/O host bridge's I/O devices. Firmware will continue boot but will not configure the I/O devices connected to the specified I/O host bridge. Such I/O devices will not be usable as console nor boot devices but might be usable by the O/S. Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoPciMappingTooBig.name: hpevtIoPciMappingTooBig
hpevtIoPciMappingTooBig.description: The total resource requirement from the I/O devices connected to an I/O host bridge exceeds the resource limit of the I/O host bridge. Firmware will continue boot but will not configure the I/O devices connected to the specified I/O host bridge. In addition, firmware will display the following EFI warning message, 'Insufficient resources to assign to one or more I/O devices.' Such I/O devices will not be usable as console nor boot devices but might be usable by the O/S. Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoPciUnmappingFailed.name: hpevtIoPciUnmappingFailed
hpevtIoPciUnmappingFailed.description: Firmware encountered an unexpected error while attempting to clear resource allocations on an I/O host bridge's I/O devices. Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoPcixcapSampleError.name: hpevtIoPcixcapSampleError
hpevtIoPcixcapSampleError.description: An I/O host bridge failed to determine the appropriate PCI[X] mode and frequency (PCI, PCI-X 66 MHz, PCI-X 133 MHz, etc.) for its bus. Firmware will deconfigure the I/O host bridge and display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the failed I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoPmNotRespondingError.name: hpevtIoPmNotRespondingError
hpevtIoPmNotRespondingError.description: Firmware is unable to access the power monitor. Firmware will assume that there is sufficient power and proceed to power on an I/O slot. Data Field: Physical location of the I/O slot.

hpevtIoRopeResetError.name: hpevtIoRopeResetError
hpevtIoRopeResetError.description: An I/O controller rope reset did not complete within the expected time limit. Firmware will deconfigure the I/O host bridge attached to the rope. Data Field: Physical location of the deconfigured I/O host bridge.

hpevtIoSbaClearErrFailed.name: hpevtIoSbaClearErrFailed
hpevtIoSbaClearErrFailed.description: During I/O chipset configuration, firmware found a persistent error condition. Firmware will attempt to continue the boot. Data Field: Physical location of the I/O chipset.

hpevtIoSlotPowerDefaultError.name: hpevtIoSlotPowerDefaultError
hpevtIoSlotPowerDefaultError.description: During boot, firmware has found a hot-plug I/O slot with an incorrect default power state. The slot power should be off by default. Data Field: Physical location of the I/O slot.

hpevtIoSlotPowerOnError.name: hpevtIoSlotPowerOnError
hpevtIoSlotPowerOnError.description: Firmware encountered an error while attempting to power on an I/O slot. Firmware will deconfigure the I/O slot and display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the I/O slot.

hpevtIoSlotStandbyPowerError.name: hpevtIoSlotStandbyPowerError
hpevtIoSlotStandbyPowerError.description: An I/O slot's standby (Vaux) power has failed. Firmware will deconfigure the I/O slot and display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the failed I/O slot.

hpevtIoUnknownPcixcapVal.name: hpevtIoUnknownPcixcapVal
hpevtIoUnknownPcixcapVal.description: An I/O host bridge or hot-plug controller reported an illegal PCI[X] bus mode for its bus or slot, respectively. Firmware will deconfigure the I/O host bridge or I/O slot and display the following EFI warning, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the failed I/O host bridge or the failed I/O slot.

hpevtIoUnsupRopeFreq.name: hpevtIoUnsupRopeFreq
hpevtIoUnsupRopeFreq.description: Firmware attempted to configure an I/O controller rope to an unsupported frequency. Firmware will deconfigure any I/O host bridge connected to the rope and display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the failed rope.

hpevtIoUnsupportedLba.name: hpevtIoUnsupportedLba
hpevtIoUnsupportedLba.description: Firmware has found an unsupported I/O host bridge type. Firmware will deconfigure the I/O host bridge and display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the I/O host bridge.

hpevtMcInitiated.name: hpevtMcInitiated
hpevtMcInitiated.description: A Machine Check has been initiated

hpevtMdtConstructAreaBad.name: hpevtMdtConstructAreaBad
hpevtMdtConstructAreaBad.description: There has been a problem building the Memory Data Table (MDT).

hpevtMdtLmmioEntryNotFound.name: hpevtMdtLmmioEntryNotFound
hpevtMdtLmmioEntryNotFound.description: There has been a problem building the Memory Data Table (MDT).

hpevtMdtPageZeroBad.name: hpevtMdtPageZeroBad
hpevtMdtPageZeroBad.description: Memory page 0 was slated for deallocation in the PDT. EFI cannot launch with page 0 bad, so the system will halt.

hpevtMdtUnableToFindSpace.name: hpevtMdtUnableToFindSpace
hpevtMdtUnableToFindSpace.description: There has been a problem building the Memory Data Table (MDT).

hpevtMediaFailure.name: hpevtMediaFailure
hpevtMediaFailure.description: There has been a media failure.

hpevtMemBibRegFailure.name: hpevtMemBibRegFailure
hpevtMemBibRegFailure.description: Indicates that the chipset register test has failed. The data field contains the physical address of the failing register.

hpevtMemCacheLine0WrRdFailed.name: hpevtMemCacheLine0WrRdFailed
hpevtMemCacheLine0WrRdFailed.description: After FW's first access to main memory, FW detected that the CEC logged an error after reading back what was just written.

hpevtMemDimmLoadOrderErr.name: hpevtMemDimmLoadOrderErr
hpevtMemDimmLoadOrderErr.description: A DIMM that is required to be loaded in order for this DIMM to function properly is not loaded, so FW will deallocate this DIMM. Currently, none of the platforms require any DIMMs to be loaded in order for this DIMM to work properly.

hpevtMemDimmSpdChecksum.name: hpevtMemDimmSpdChecksum
hpevtMemDimmSpdChecksum.description: The DIMM specified by the physical location has an SPD EEPROM that has a bad checksum. The Data field is the physical location of the DIMM.

hpevtMemDimmSpdFatal.name: hpevtMemDimmSpdFatal
hpevtMemDimmSpdFatal.description: Detected a error in DIMM SPD

hpevtMemDimmTypeIncompatible.name: hpevtMemDimmTypeIncompatible
hpevtMemDimmTypeIncompatible.description: A DIMM was installed whose DIMM type is not compatible with the current set of supported DIMMs for this platform.

hpevtMemDimmTypeMismatch.name: hpevtMemDimmTypeMismatch
hpevtMemDimmTypeMismatch.description: The DIMM type of this DIMM is not the same as the other DIMMs in the same group. The group of DIMMs is deallocated. If this is the last active group of DIMMs in the system, the system is halted.

hpevtMemDimmTypeTableFull.name: hpevtMemDimmTypeTableFull
hpevtMemDimmTypeTableFull.description: The DIMM type table is full

hpevtMemDmtEntryNotFound.name: hpevtMemDmtEntryNotFound
hpevtMemDmtEntryNotFound.description: An entry for the DIMM was not found in the DMT table. The data field contains the DMT entry that the caller wanted to find (in Dimm number format, which is 2 bytes, upper byte is the extender number, lower byte is the chip select of the rank caller is looking for.)

hpevtMemEccMbeDataTstFailed.name: hpevtMemEccMbeDataTstFailed
hpevtMemEccMbeDataTstFailed.description: The FW selftest of CEC multi-bit error (MBE) detection has failed. The upper 32 bits of the data field contain the Dword offset within the cacheline of the failed MBE detection. The lower 32 bits are split in two, and they contain the bit numbers within the Dword that were flipped in order to cause an MBE.

hpevtMemEccMbeSignalTstFailed.name: hpevtMemEccMbeSignalTstFailed
hpevtMemEccMbeSignalTstFailed.description: The FW selftest of CEC multi-bit error (MBE) signaling has failed. The upper 32 bits of the data field contain the Dword offset within the cacheline of the failed MBE detection. The lower 32 bits are split in two, and they contain the bit numbers within the Dword that were flipped in order to cause an MBE.

hpevtMemEccSbeDataTstFailed.name: hpevtMemEccSbeDataTstFailed
hpevtMemEccSbeDataTstFailed.description: The FW selftest of CEC single-bit error (SBE) detection has failed. The data field contains the bit within the Dword that was flipped that caused the CEC to not see an SBE.

hpevtMemEccSbeEccTstFailed.name: hpevtMemEccSbeEccTstFailed
hpevtMemEccSbeEccTstFailed.description: The FW selftest of CEC single-bit error (SBE) detection has failed. The data field contains the bit within the Dword that was flipped that caused the CEC to not see an SBE.

hpevtMemEnoughMemFailed.name: hpevtMemEnoughMemFailed
hpevtMemEnoughMemFailed.description: Memory FW detected errors below 1MB. FW will not allow boot in this case, so memory FW will reinterleave and retest.

hpevtMemErrAddrNotInMbat.name: hpevtMemErrAddrNotInMbat
hpevtMemErrAddrNotInMbat.description: Memory FW could not figure out which rank maps to the physical address specified in the data field.

hpevtMemErrClearFail.name: hpevtMemErrClearFail
hpevtMemErrClearFail.description: Memory FW was unable to clear the platform error logs on the CEC. The Datafield contains the error status of the CEC.

hpevtMemErrLogFailedToClear.name: hpevtMemErrLogFailedToClear
hpevtMemErrLogFailedToClear.description: Memory FW was unable to clear the platform error logs on the CEC. The Datafield contains the error status of the CEC.

hpevtMemErrorRegClearFailure.name: hpevtMemErrorRegClearFailure
hpevtMemErrorRegClearFailure.description: The Error registers in the CEC have failed to clear. The data field contains the error status of the CEC after the attempted clear.

hpevtMemExtFatalLoadOrdErr.name: hpevtMemExtFatalLoadOrdErr
hpevtMemExtFatalLoadOrdErr.description: A DIMM that is required to be loaded in order for this DIMM to function properly is not loaded, so FW will deallocate this DIMM. Currently, none of the platforms require any DIMMs to be loaded in order for this DIMM to work properly.

hpevtMemFirmwareProb.name: hpevtMemFirmwareProb
hpevtMemFirmwareProb.description: An error occurred that memory FW does not know how to handle.

hpevtMemMainMemFailed.name: hpevtMemMainMemFailed
hpevtMemMainMemFailed.description: FW was unable to create a memory configuration with no errors in low memory to hand off to EFI.

hpevtMemMbeInRank.name: hpevtMemMbeInRank
hpevtMemMbeInRank.description: A series of MEM_MBE_IN_RANK chassis code will be sent when an error is detected by firmware. The data fields will contain information on the error based on the data type as follows: Physical Location - location of dimm(s) in error; Physical Address - address affect by error; Syndrome - Firmware generated ECC syndrome that can be used to further isolate the error.

hpevtMemMcRegFailure.name: hpevtMemMcRegFailure
hpevtMemMcRegFailure.description: The chipset's memory controller failed the register test. The data field contains the address of the register that failed selftest.

hpevtMemNoDimmsInstalled.name: hpevtMemNoDimmsInstalled
hpevtMemNoDimmsInstalled.description: Memory Discovery could not detect any DIMMs installed.

hpevtMemNoMemFound.name: hpevtMemNoMemFound
hpevtMemNoMemFound.description: FW could not continue because there are no valid memory ranks loaded.

hpevtMemPdtDisabledHalt.name: hpevtMemPdtDisabledHalt
hpevtMemPdtDisabledHalt.description: The PDT has been disabled, and FW found memory errors during selftest. This is a stopboot condition. Also, the PDT will never be disabled in customer systems, so this event should never be seen in the field.

hpevtMemPdtDisabledWarning.name: hpevtMemPdtDisabledWarning
hpevtMemPdtDisabledWarning.description: An event indicating that the user has the PDT disabled on this boot. The PDT will never be disabled in customer systems, so this event should never be seen in the field.

hpevtMemPdtNvmErr.name: hpevtMemPdtNvmErr
hpevtMemPdtNvmErr.description: Error writing entry into the PDT.

hpevtMemPdtTableFull.name: hpevtMemPdtTableFull
hpevtMemPdtTableFull.description: An attempt was made to add an entry to a full PDT. The entry is not added, and this event is sent.

hpevtMemPlatformInitFailure.name: hpevtMemPlatformInitFailure
hpevtMemPlatformInitFailure.description: Memory FW was unable to save or restore the original error configuration (including CEC error log and signal enable and CPU ECC detection). This event should never be seen in the field unless there is a FW problem

hpevtMemRankEntryNotFound.name: hpevtMemRankEntryNotFound
hpevtMemRankEntryNotFound.description: The rank structure that corresponds to the rankID in the data field could not be found in the Rank table. The Data field is the rankID of the structure it is looking for. This error event should never be seen.

hpevtMemTestExcessMcBits.name: hpevtMemTestExcessMcBits
hpevtMemTestExcessMcBits.description: More than one error type was detected when only one error type was expected.

hpevtMemTestFwdProgBitsInvalid.name: hpevtMemTestFwdProgBitsInvalid
hpevtMemTestFwdProgBitsInvalid.description: The forward progress bits that memory FW uses to track state are invalid. The data field is the fwd progress field.

hpevtMemTestStatusBitsInvalid.name: hpevtMemTestStatusBitsInvalid
hpevtMemTestStatusBitsInvalid.description: The memory error status has bits set in it that indicate another non-memory error occurred. The data field contains the CEC's error status.

hpevtMemTestSummaryBitsInvalid.name: hpevtMemTestSummaryBitsInvalid
hpevtMemTestSummaryBitsInvalid.description: The memory test summary bits are invalid. The data field is the test summary bits.

hpevtMemUnexpectedMca.name: hpevtMemUnexpectedMca
hpevtMemUnexpectedMca.description: Memory rank shadowing has been selected but is not supported by the revision of the memory controller.

hpevtMemWarnDistributionCheckBypass.name: hpevtMemWarnDistributionCheckBypass
hpevtMemWarnDistributionCheckBypass.description: The control bit to skip the DIMM distribution check is set and the DIMM distribution check was skipped. This bit should only be done in the factory and not in the field.

hpevtMemWarnLoadingOrderBypass.name: hpevtMemWarnLoadingOrderBypass
hpevtMemWarnLoadingOrderBypass.description: The control bit to skip the DIMM loading order check is set and the DIMM loading order check was skipped. This bit should only be done in the factory and not in the field.

hpevtMemWarnLoopOnDestTest.name: hpevtMemWarnLoopOnDestTest
hpevtMemWarnLoopOnDestTest.description: The control bit to loop on destructive memory test is set and the destructive memory tests are run continuously. This bit should only be done in the factory and not in the field.

hpevtMemWarnSetCheckBypass.name: hpevtMemWarnSetCheckBypass
hpevtMemWarnSetCheckBypass.description: The control bit to skip the DIMM set check is set and the DIMM set check was skipped. This bit should only be done in the factory and not in the field.

hpevtMemWarnSpdBypass.name: hpevtMemWarnSpdBypass
hpevtMemWarnSpdBypass.description: The control bit to skip the DIMM SPD check is set and the checking of the DIMM SPD was skipped. This bit should only be done in the factory and not in the field.

hpevtMemWarnUsingAltConfig.name: hpevtMemWarnUsingAltConfig
hpevtMemWarnUsingAltConfig.description: The control bit to load an alternate memory configuration is set and an alternate memory configuration has been loaded. This bit should only be set in the factory and not in the field.

hpevtOsInitNotRegistered.name: hpevtOsInitNotRegistered
hpevtOsInitNotRegistered.description: The OS_INIT vector has not been registered

hpevtOsMcaNotRegistered.name: hpevtOsMcaNotRegistered
hpevtOsMcaNotRegistered.description: The OS_MCA vector has not been registered

hpevtOsMcaUncorrectedMc.name: hpevtOsMcaUncorrectedMc
hpevtOsMcaUncorrectedMc.description: An Uncorrected Machine Check has occurred

hpevtSalCheckUnknownFail.name: hpevtSalCheckUnknownFail
hpevtSalCheckUnknownFail.description: The handler for SAL_CHECK has failed for an unknown reason.

hpevtSalInitUnknownFail.name: hpevtSalInitUnknownFail
hpevtSalInitUnknownFail.description: The handler for SAL_INIT has failed for an unknown reason.

hpevtUndefinedSmcInterleaveErr.name: hpevtUndefinedSmcInterleaveErr
hpevtUndefinedSmcInterleaveErr.description: Indicates that FW encountered a Fatal interleaving error. The data field contains the return status from the interleaving procedure call.

hpevtUnexpectedRetToSalInit.name: hpevtUnexpectedRetToSalInit
hpevtUnexpectedRetToSalInit.description: The SFW TOC vector (SAL_INIT) has been unexpectedly returned to.

hpevtFwInstalledCpuDegraded.name: hpevtFwInstalledCpuDegraded
hpevtFwInstalledCpuDegraded.description: Firmware is adding a device tree node for a CPU that is degraded in functionality. The cpu should not be trusted and will not be active in the system.

hpevtPdRendezTreeError.name: hpevtPdRendezTreeError
hpevtPdRendezTreeError.description: Firmware was unable to locate a required element in the device tree and cannot create a partition. The resource that cannot be located is listed as an ansi string in the data field.

hpevtPdCellConfigError.name: hpevtPdCellConfigError
hpevtPdCellConfigError.description: The currently executing cell is not configured to be part of the cell set it is attempting to rendezvous with.

hpevtPdRemoteCsrReadError.name: hpevtPdRemoteCsrReadError
hpevtPdRemoteCsrReadError.description: The current cell could not read a remote cells CSR. The remote cell number is displayed in the data field. These cells will not be able to rendezvous.

hpevtPdCellLateForRendez.name: hpevtPdCellLateForRendez
hpevtPdCellLateForRendez.description: The currently executing cell arrived too late to rendezvous with the other cells described in the complex profile as cells it should rendezvous with.

hpevtPdIncompatibleCpuTypes.name: hpevtPdIncompatibleCpuTypes
hpevtPdIncompatibleCpuTypes.description: The currently executing cell detected CPUs that are incompatible with it to be installed on a cell that the current cell is trying to rendezvous with.

hpevtPdCellLateLocalRendezSet.name: hpevtPdCellLateLocalRendezSet
hpevtPdCellLateLocalRendezSet.description: The current cell was too slow creating the local rendezvous set and the other cells have left it behind. It will not be able to participate in the remainder of the rendezvous. The data field is unused, but the cell emitting this event is the one too late to rendezvous.

hpevtCellNotInGlobalSet.name: hpevtCellNotInGlobalSet
hpevtCellNotInGlobalSet.description: The reporting cell was not included in the final global set that was agreed upon. This means that another cell either could not reach the reporting cell or the reporting cell was too late arriving to a required state.

hpevtNoViableCoreCellInPd.name: hpevtNoViableCoreCellInPd
hpevtNoViableCoreCellInPd.description: No cells in the PD can be a core cell. This is fatal.

hpevtErrorPromotingCoreCell.name: hpevtErrorPromotingCoreCell
hpevtErrorPromotingCoreCell.description: System Firmware was unable to notify utilities of the selected core cell number.

hpevtFabricNoServiceProviders.name: hpevtFabricNoServiceProviders
hpevtFabricNoServiceProviders.description: The fabric code is unable to find a service provider for a required banyan service.

hpevtFabricPortError.name: hpevtFabricPortError
hpevtFabricPortError.description: The fabric port specified in the data field had an error.

hpevtFabricReadError.name: hpevtFabricReadError
hpevtFabricReadError.description: An error occurred reading a CSR. The CSR address is displayed in the data field.

hpevtFabricWriteError.name: hpevtFabricWriteError
hpevtFabricWriteError.description: Error writing to Fabric. CSR data in data field.

hpevtXbcSlicesHwVersionDiffer.name: hpevtXbcSlicesHwVersionDiffer
hpevtXbcSlicesHwVersionDiffer.description: Incompatible crossbar slices are installed The data field is the two revisions reported by slice1 and slice0 of the CSR data. Bits [31:0] slice0 revision Bits [63:32] slice1 revision

hpevtXbcSlicesInDiffLocation.name: hpevtXbcSlicesInDiffLocation
hpevtXbcSlicesInDiffLocation.description: Crossbar slices are in different locations. The data field is the two locations reported by slice1 and slice0 of the CSR data.

hpevtMonarchTakeover.name: hpevtMonarchTakeover
hpevtMonarchTakeover.description: A CPU has taken over as the monarch CPU.

hpevtDeadSram.name: hpevtDeadSram
hpevtDeadSram.description: SRAM cannot be accessed on the cell board. Execution cannot continue.

hpevtDeadDillon.name: hpevtDeadDillon
hpevtDeadDillon.description: The PDH Arbiter component/chip cannot be located or used.

hpevtDeadPdhHw.name: hpevtDeadPdhHw
hpevtDeadPdhHw.description: A required piece of PDH bus hardware cannot be contacted.

hpevtIoPciBusMixedSpeeds.name: hpevtIoPciBusMixedSpeeds
hpevtIoPciBusMixedSpeeds.description: The physical location of the PCI controller with mixed speeds is displayed in the data field.

hpevtIoPciBusDepthExceeded.name: hpevtIoPciBusDepthExceeded
hpevtIoPciBusDepthExceeded.description: During walking of the IO busses, the maximum depth was exceeded. This is a hardware configuration problem. The data field contains the physical location.

hpevtlotimeout.name: hpevtlotimeout
hpevtlotimeout.description: A Timeout occurred during RI initialization. The CSR is in the data field. The alert level will vary.

hpevtIoBuswalkSuperio.name: hpevtIoBuswalkSuperio
hpevtIoBuswalkSuperio.description: SuperIO has been detected in the PCI slot displayed in the data field.

hpevtIoSbaCorrDataParityErr.name: hpevtIoSbaCorrDataParityErr
hpevtIoSbaCorrDataParityErr.description: IO Link Software error was corrected.

hpevtIoSbaFatalDataParityErr.name: hpevtIoSbaFatalDataParityErr
hpevtIoSbaFatalDataParityErr.description: Parity error in Reg FIFO Internal parity error.

hpevtIoSbaFatalParityErr.name: hpevtIoSbaFatalParityErr
hpevtIoSbaFatalParityErr.description: LBA to SBA parity error on command, rope will go fatal.

hpevtIoSbaFatalMapErr.name: hpevtIoSbaFatalMapErr
hpevtIoSbaFatalMapErr.description: Access to invalid TLB entry Requesting rope fatal.

hpevtIoLbaInitErr.name: hpevtIoLbaInitErr
hpevtIoLbaInitErr.description: An error was encountered when initing the rope number specified in the data field.

hpevtIoLbaCorrTimeoutErr.name: hpevtIoLbaCorrTimeoutErr
hpevtIoLbaCorrTimeoutErr.description: LBA correctable timeout error was encountered.

hpevtIoLbaUncFunctionErr.name: hpevtIoLbaUncFunctionErr
hpevtIoLbaUncFunctionErr.description: LBA uncorrectable Function Error was encountered.

hpevtIoLbaUncTimeoutErr.name: hpevtIoLbaUncTimeoutErr
hpevtIoLbaUncTimeoutErr.description: LBA uncorrectable Timeout Error was encountered.

hpevtIoLbaMiscUncErr.name: hpevtIoLbaMiscUncErr
hpevtIoLbaMiscUncErr.description: Misc uncorrectable error discovered on LBA.

hpevtIoLbaUncParityErr.name: hpevtIoLbaUncParityErr
hpevtIoLbaUncParityErr.description: LBA encountered an uncorrectable parity error.

hpevtIoDevAdapterMiscUncErr.name: hpevtIoDevAdapterMiscUncErr
hpevtIoDevAdapterMiscUncErr.description: Misc Uncorrectable Error encountered on the card specified in the data field.

hpevtIoDevAdapterMiscFatalErr.name: hpevtIoDevAdapterMiscFatalErr
hpevtIoDevAdapterMiscFatalErr.description: Misc fatal error was discovered on the PCI card specified in the data field.

hpevtMemDimmSpdExtendedChecksum.name: hpevtMemDimmSpdExtendedChecksum
hpevtMemDimmSpdExtendedChecksum.description: The calculated and compared Checksums of the SPD EEPROM don't match.

hpevtOptsHdrCksumError.name: hpevtOptsHdrCksumError
hpevtOptsHdrCksumError.description: The Options component encountered a header checksum error. The actual data is in the data field of the chassis code.

hpevtOptsDataCksumError.name: hpevtOptsDataCksumError
hpevtOptsDataCksumError.description: The Options service data had a bad checksum. Actual data is in the data field.

hpevtPdMemIntlvWaysMismatch.name: hpevtPdMemIntlvWaysMismatch
hpevtPdMemIntlvWaysMismatch.description: Internal inconsistency in the interleave tables.

hpevtPdMemUnintlvdMemory.name: hpevtPdMemUnintlvdMemory
hpevtPdMemUnintlvdMemory.description: The CellInfoList is not null and was expected to be. There has been an error in interleaving.

hpevtPdMemNoMemoryDesc.name: hpevtPdMemNoMemoryDesc
hpevtPdMemNoMemoryDesc.description: Error in constructing the Memory Descriptor.

hpevtPdMemUpdateLocalCellFailed.name: hpevtPdMemUpdateLocalCellFailed
hpevtPdMemUpdateLocalCellFailed.description: Unable to update the local memory layout.

hpevtPdMemPdtAddrNotFound.name: hpevtPdMemPdtAddrNotFound
hpevtPdMemPdtAddrNotFound.description: A required address was not found within a mapped address in the PDT.

hpevtPdMemPdtInstallFail.name: hpevtPdMemPdtInstallFail
hpevtPdMemPdtInstallFail.description: Failure to install a partition level PDT. Errors prevented it.

hpevtUnusableResource.name: hpevtUnusableResource
hpevtUnusableResource.description: A critical resource that is required early in the initialization process either could not be found, or was unusable. The specific resource is specified in the data field as follows: Platform Parameters Component not found in FIT: 0xdead0001; SRAM_BASE not found in platform parms: 0xdead0002; SRAM_SIZE not found in Platform Parms: 0xdead0003; firmware framework not found in the fit: 0xdead0004; Framework Segment not usable: 0xdead0005; bad NVRAM: 0xdead0006; PDH Arbiter unusable: 0xdead0007; SRAM unusable: 0xdead0008; CPU unusable: 0xdead0009; Options Component Unusable: 0xdead000a; Real Time Clock unusable: DEAD_RTC; Unknown: 0xdead0086

hpevtFwError.name: hpevtFwError
hpevtFwError.description: An internal firmware error was encountered. This is usually caused by a bad parameter passed to a function, corrupt memory, corrupt malloc tables or something similar. The data field contains the IP address of the function that encountered the error.

hpevtNvramDataCmpError.name: hpevtNvramDataCmpError
hpevtNvramDataCmpError.description: NVRAM failed with a data compare error. 3 chassis codes will be sent. The first one will have the expected data and the second the actual data and the third one will be the address.

hpevtNvramCrcError.name: hpevtNvramCrcError
hpevtNvramCrcError.description: An NVRAM CRC Error was detected. There will always be 2 chassis codes sent. The first one will give the expected data and the second the actual data.

hpevtErm.name: hpevtErm
hpevtErm.description: Get Error Response Mode has been called. The first 8 bytes of the response mode string are displayed in the data field and must be converted to ASCII from the hex values.

hpevtErrorObtainingSemaphore.name: hpevtErrorObtainingSemaphore
hpevtErrorObtainingSemaphore.description: The required semaphore could not be obtained due to errors. The data field contains the IP of the routine trying to obtain the semaphore. A request was placed for more NVRAM to be allocated but NVRAM was full.

hpevtNvramBlockRevMismatch.name: hpevtNvramBlockRevMismatch
hpevtNvramBlockRevMismatch.description: The NVRAM block requested has an unexpected revision. This chassis code will be emitted in pairs. The first one will contain the expected revision number, the second will contain the actual revision number.

hpevtNvramBlockNotFound.name: hpevtNvramBlockNotFound
hpevtNvramBlockNotFound.description: The requested NVRAM block was not found. The ID that was not found is displayed in the data field.

hpevtNvramBlockLocked.name: hpevtNvramBlockLocked
hpevtNvramBlockLocked.description: The block id specified in the data field is locked.

hpevtNvramBlockUnlocked.name: hpevtNvramBlockUnlocked
hpevtNvramBlockUnlocked.description: Firmware tried to unlock a NVRAM block that was already unlocked. Data field contains the block ID.

hpevtNvramHeaderNotFound.name: hpevtNvramHeaderNotFound
hpevtNvramHeaderNotFound.description: The header in the NVRAM space was not found.

hpevtNvmFreelistCorrupt.name: hpevtNvmFreelistCorrupt
hpevtNvmFreelistCorrupt.description: The Freelist used vor Non-Volatile Memory allocation is corrpt.

hpevtResetForReconfig.name: hpevtResetForReconfig
hpevtResetForReconfig.description: System firmware has detected a condition that requires the cell to be reset for reconfiguration. The function has been called and is now executing. Data field contains the cell number being reset.

hpevtPdRendezUtilityError.name: hpevtPdRendezUtilityError
hpevtPdRendezUtilityError.description: During PD rendezvous, system firmware encountered a problem sending commands to the utilities system. This will prevent a fully functional PD from being created.

hpevtHalt.name: hpevtHalt
hpevtHalt.description: System Firmware has determined that cell or system progress must be halted. The data field contains the Instruction Pointer of the function that called for the halt. The second instance of this code being emitted indicates the major state in system change. This code must be emitted in pairs.

hpevtDuiNoConsole.name: hpevtDuiNoConsole
hpevtDuiNoConsole.description: The DUI (Developers User Interface) was entered, but there is no console available for the interface.

hpevtErrorProcFailed.name: hpevtErrorProcFailed
hpevtErrorProcFailed.description: During Error processing and reporting, an error was detected that prevented further processing of errors. The data field contains an ASCII message indicating the problem.

hpevtReconfigResetFail.name: hpevtReconfigResetFail
hpevtReconfigResetFail.description: System firmware is unable to complete the request to reset the cell for reconfiguration. Typically, are required step has not been performed yet or a needed resource is unavailable.

hpevtPdErrorReachableSet.name: hpevtPdErrorReachableSet
hpevtPdErrorReachableSet.description: The cell was not able to reach all the other cells in its configured set through the fabric. The data field contains the bitmask of actual cells that were reached.

hpevtIoBridgeDepthExceeded.name: hpevtIoBridgeDepthExceeded
hpevtIoBridgeDepthExceeded.description: Firmware detected a PCI-to-PCI bridge that exceeds the maximum supported bridge depth. Firmware will not configure I/O devices below the maximum bridge depth. Such I/O devices will not be usable as console nor boot devices but might be usable by the O/S. Data Field: PCI function address of the bridge that exceeded the maximum depth limit. Bits 24..31: segment number Bits 16..23: bus number Bits 11..15: device number Bits 8..10: function number Bits 0..7: reserved (0)

hpevtEfiConsoleDriverError.name: hpevtEfiConsoleDriverError
hpevtEfiConsoleDriverError.description: Debugging event, not for release. This event is no longer used on Everest/xPeak systems but its event ID is still contained in the code base.

hpevtRemoteCellStateUnknown.name: hpevtRemoteCellStateUnknown
hpevtRemoteCellStateUnknown.description: The reporting cell read an unknown state from a remote cell. This chassis code will be emitted in pairs. The first one indicating the cell number in the data field and the second code indicating the state read in the data field.

hpevtPdMltplCoreCells.name: hpevtPdMltplCoreCells
hpevtPdMltplCoreCells.description: The reporting Cell thinks that it should be the core cell but has discovered another cell in the same PD that thinks it should be the core cell. This is a serious problem.

hpevtUtilSendCommandError.name: hpevtUtilSendCommandError
hpevtUtilSendCommandError.description: The utilities system firmware component received an error response from the SINC in response to a command being sent. The exact error is displayed in the data field. Typically, this can occur when the SINC cannot talk to the MP.

hpevtUtilCellSlotError.name: hpevtUtilCellSlotError
hpevtUtilCellSlotError.description: System Firmware issued the Retrieve Cell Slot State command to the Sync and got an error back. See related chassis code or the specifics of the error.

hpevtMcCellRendezFailed.name: hpevtMcCellRendezFailed
hpevtMcCellRendezFailed.description: This denotes the fact that all the cpus in the cell did not rendezvous.

hpevtMcNoAccessToPd.name: hpevtMcNoAccessToPd
hpevtMcNoAccessToPd.description: This chassis code indicates that the cell does not have any access to a PD.

hpevtMcLossOfLockstep.name: hpevtMcLossOfLockstep
hpevtMcLossOfLockstep.description: This indicates the cell would not be able to join the other cells in the PD level rendezvous. The data portion represents the cell id of the cell that incurred the loss of lockstep.

hpevtMcPdCellRendezFailed.name: hpevtMcPdCellRendezFailed
hpevtMcPdCellRendezFailed.description: This indicates that some of the cells did not show up during the PD level rendezvous.

hpevtMcProcErrHalt.name: hpevtMcProcErrHalt
hpevtMcProcErrHalt.description: This indicates that catastrophic errors have been found in the PIN block of the cell controller. The cell needs to be reset/ halt.

hpevtMcCellMonarchTimeout.name: hpevtMcCellMonarchTimeout
hpevtMcCellMonarchTimeout.description: This means that the cell monach cpu has not completed the assigned task within the timeout and hence it will be deconfigured.

hpevtMcPdCellMissedRendez.name: hpevtMcPdCellMissedRendez
hpevtMcPdCellMissedRendez.description: This indicates that the cell is too late for the PD level rendezvous. And hence it will not join the other PD cells.

hpevtMcPdMonarchTimeout.name: hpevtMcPdMonarchTimeout
hpevtMcPdMonarchTimeout.description: This indicates the state where the PD monarch was not able to complete the task within a certain time. It failed.

hpevtRemoteSetViewRootError.name: hpevtRemoteSetViewRootError
hpevtRemoteSetViewRootError.description: System firmware on the Core cell was unable to update a slave cell with the location of the root of the partition tree. The CPU that was unable to be contacted is printed in the data field.

hpevtCsrTestFailure.name: hpevtCsrTestFailure
hpevtCsrTestFailure.description: Read test on a CSR failed and the CSR contents were not updated. This chassis code will be emitted in 3's, with the CSR Address, expected data, and actual data given.

hpevtPdMemGetIcmInfoFailed.name: hpevtPdMemGetIcmInfoFailed
hpevtPdMemGetIcmInfoFailed.description: This chassis code reports the failure in collecting the ICM parameters needed for the cell interleaving.

hpevtPdMemGetCellInfoFailed.name: hpevtPdMemGetCellInfoFailed
hpevtPdMemGetCellInfoFailed.description: This chassis code indicates that the cell interleaving routine could not get the information on the cell memory.

hpevtPdMemUpdateCellGniFailed.name: hpevtPdMemUpdateCellGniFailed
hpevtPdMemUpdateCellGniFailed.description: This chassis code is used to represent the failure in updating the GNI information of the cell with the CLM ( cell local memory) information obtained from the Complex Profile.

hpevtPdMemAdjustMinZiFailed.name: hpevtPdMemAdjustMinZiFailed
hpevtPdMemAdjustMinZiFailed.description: This represents the failure in adjusting the memory information with the minimum ZI requirements.

hpevtStableProfileXsumError.name: hpevtStableProfileXsumError
hpevtStableProfileXsumError.description: Complex Profile A (Stable Profile) stored checksum does not match the calculated checksum. The expected data and actual data are displayed in the 2 reporting event Ids.

hpevtDynamicProfileXsumError.name: hpevtDynamicProfileXsumError
hpevtDynamicProfileXsumError.description: The Dynamic Complex Profile (Group B) stored checksum did not equal the calculated checksum. The Expected Data and Actual date are displayed in successive chassis codes.

hpevtPartitionProfileXsumError.name: hpevtPartitionProfileXsumError
hpevtPartitionProfileXsumError.description: The stored value of the complex profile Group C does not match the calculated value. Expected data and actual data are stored in successive chassis codes.

hpevtStableProfileSeqidInvalid.name: hpevtStableProfileSeqidInvalid
hpevtStableProfileSeqidInvalid.description: The Complex Profile Group A sequence ID is invalid. Booting cannot continue. The actual data is in the chassis code data field.

hpevtDynamicProfileSeqidInvalid.name: hpevtDynamicProfileSeqidInvalid
hpevtDynamicProfileSeqidInvalid.description: The Dynamic Complex Profile (Group B) sequence ID is invalid. The invalid Sequence ID is displayed in the data field.

hpevtPartitionProfileSeqidInvalid.name: hpevtPartitionProfileSeqidInvalid
hpevtPartitionProfileSeqidInvalid.description: The Group C Partition Complex Profile Sequence ID is invalid. The value read is displayed in the data field.

hpevtEfiFwError.name: hpevtEfiFwError
hpevtEfiFwError.description: An internal EFI firmware error was encountered. This is usually caused by a bad parameter passed to a function, corrupt memory, corrupt malloc, corrupt firmware tree or something similar. The data field contains the IP address of the function that encountered the error.

hpevtCmplxProfilePdNumMismatch.name: hpevtCmplxProfilePdNumMismatch
hpevtCmplxProfilePdNumMismatch.description: The Complex Profile Group A PD assignment for this cell does not match the PD or Partition number in Group C of the complex profile. This is a fatal condition for the cell. The PD number from group A will be emitted first, followed by a subsequent code for the PD assigned in group C.

hpevtCmplxProfilePdNumInvalid.name: hpevtCmplxProfilePdNumInvalid
hpevtCmplxProfilePdNumInvalid.description: The Partition (PD) assigned to this cell in the complex profile group A and C is larger than the maximum allowed number of PDs as specified by Group A.

hpevtXbcPortSm4Error.name: hpevtXbcPortSm4Error
hpevtXbcPortSm4Error.description: Tried to obtain the port semaphore but GetPortSemaphore returned an ERROR. Could be a failed write to the port semaphore crossbar CSR or another cell owned the semaphore. Data field bits 32:63 contain the crossbar ID and bits 0:31 contain the port number for which the semaphore was being obtained.

hpevtXbcPortSm4NotReleased.name: hpevtXbcPortSm4NotReleased
hpevtXbcPortSm4NotReleased.description: Currently owned the port semaphore but could not release the semaphore. Data field bits 32:63 contain the crossbar ID and bits 0:32 contain the port number.

hpevtBootBmcTokenUploadFailure.name: hpevtBootBmcTokenUploadFailure
hpevtBootBmcTokenUploadFailure.description: There was an error reading from the BMC token when attempting to write to SAL NVM. This is a stop boot condition. Data: Lower 32 bits, BMC Token Number. Upper 32 bits, bmc return status.

hpevtBootNvmTokenAccessFailure.name: hpevtBootNvmTokenAccessFailure
hpevtBootNvmTokenAccessFailure.description: The read from SAL NVM has failed. This is a stop boot condition. Data: The token number on which the read failed

hpevtBootBmcTokenDownloadError.name: hpevtBootBmcTokenDownloadError
hpevtBootBmcTokenDownloadError.description: There was an error when trying to write to a BMC Token. This is a boot warning condition. Data: lower 32 bits are BMC token number, upper 32 bits is the status return from the BMC.

hpevtBootErrorWritingFirstBootToken.name: hpevtBootErrorWritingFirstBootToken
hpevtBootErrorWritingFirstBootToken.description: There has been an error writing the BMC_FIRST_BOOT token. This is a stop boot condition.

hpevtBootFruReadError.name: hpevtBootFruReadError
hpevtBootFruReadError.description: The read of a FRU has failed. Data: Device ID of device that failed the FRU read.

hpevtBootFruXsumError.name: hpevtBootFruXsumError
hpevtBootFruXsumError.description: The read of a FRU has failed the checksum test. Data: Device ID of device that failed the FRU read.

hpevtBootFruVersionError.name: hpevtBootFruVersionError
hpevtBootFruVersionError.description: The read of a FRU has failed due to a version problem. Data: Device ID of device that failed the FRU read.

hpevtBootRomRevToFitRevWarning.name: hpevtBootRomRevToFitRevWarning
hpevtBootRomRevToFitRevWarning.description: A ROM Rev and FIT Rev do not match. Data: Code for what didn't match: 0x1 = PAL_A, 0x2 = PAL_B, 0x4 = SAL_A, 0x8 = ACPI, 0xA = EFI

hpevtBootRomRevToRevBlockWarning.name: hpevtBootRomRevToRevBlockWarning
hpevtBootRomRevToRevBlockWarning.description: A ROM Rev and Rev Block do not match. Data: Code for what didn't match: 0x3 = PAL, 0x5 = SAL_A, 0x7 = SAL_B, 0x9 = ACPI, 0xB = EFI, 0xC = BMC

hpevtErrorUpdatingGroupBProfile.name: hpevtErrorUpdatingGroupBProfile
hpevtErrorUpdatingGroupBProfile.description: Firmware tried to default the Dynamic (Group B) complex profile and encountered an error.

hpevtIoPciPerr.name: hpevtIoPciPerr
hpevtIoPciPerr.description: An I/O device (or host bridge) detected a bus parity error. An I/O device (or host bridge) mastered a bus transaction and received a parity error response from the target. Data Field: Physical location of the I/O device (or host bridge).

hpevtIoPciSerr.name: hpevtIoPciSerr
hpevtIoPciSerr.description: An I/O device (or host bridge) detected an internal error. An I/O device (or host bridge) detected a bus error. Data Field: Physical location of the I/O device (or host bridge).

hpevtIoCheckLbaDeconfigErr.name: hpevtIoCheckLbaDeconfigErr
hpevtIoCheckLbaDeconfigErr.description: Firmware has deconfigured an I/O host bridge due to an error (see earlier error event). Firmware will display the following EFI warning message, 'Failed I/O slot(s) deconfigured.' Data Field: Physical location of the deconfigured I/O host bridge.

hpevtErrorUpdatingGroupCProfile.name: hpevtErrorUpdatingGroupCProfile
hpevtErrorUpdatingGroupCProfile.description: Firmware tried to default the Partition (Group C) complex profile and encountered an error.

hpevtCellNotInAPd.name: hpevtCellNotInAPd
hpevtCellNotInAPd.description: The Reporting Cell is not configured to be in a PD, according to Complex Profile Group A.

hpevtMemDimmThermalLoadOrderWarn.name: hpevtMemDimmThermalLoadOrderWarn
hpevtMemDimmThermalLoadOrderWarn.description: DIMMs are not loaded on the extender in a thermally optimal way. Boot is still possible, but the DIMM arrangement should be changed to the loading order recommended in the users manual. The data field indicates the number of the extender with incorrectly loaded DIMMs.

hpevtCellMajorityNotPresent.name: hpevtCellMajorityNotPresent
hpevtCellMajorityNotPresent.description: Not enough cells made the Rendezvous for boot to continue. The rules are listed in the cause action section.

hpevtInitRendezvousSlavesFail.name: hpevtInitRendezvousSlavesFail
hpevtInitRendezvousSlavesFail.description: SFW's INIT handler failed to rendezvous the processors.

hpevtMcIoClearFail.name: hpevtMcIoClearFail
hpevtMcIoClearFail.description: SFW's Machine Check Handler was unable to log or clear I/O error registers.

hpevtMcPalCantEscalateToBerr.name: hpevtMcPalCantEscalateToBerr
hpevtMcPalCantEscalateToBerr.description: Cannot escalate an MCA to BERR

hpevtMcPalCantEscalateToBinit.name: hpevtMcPalCantEscalateToBinit
hpevtMcPalCantEscalateToBinit.description: Cannot escalate an MCA to BINIT.

hpevtMcPalGetFeatFail.name: hpevtMcPalGetFeatFail
hpevtMcPalGetFeatFail.description: SFW failed to get the feature set from PAL.

hpevtMcPalRendFail.name: hpevtMcPalRendFail
hpevtMcPalRendFail.description: PAL Failed to rendezvous the processors during a MCA.

hpevtMcPalSetFeatFail.name: hpevtMcPalSetFeatFail
hpevtMcPalSetFeatFail.description: SFW failed to get the feature set from PAL.

hpevtMcRendezvousSlavesFail.name: hpevtMcRendezvousSlavesFail
hpevtMcRendezvousSlavesFail.description: SFW's MCA Handler has failed to rendezvous all the slaves Data: Return from the rendezvous call.

hpevtMcRendezBadVectRange.name: hpevtMcRendezBadVectRange
hpevtMcRendezBadVectRange.description: A bad rendezvous vector has been registered.

hpevtMcRendezNoMonarch.name: hpevtMcRendezNoMonarch
hpevtMcRendezNoMonarch.description: No Machine Check Monarch exists, exiting MC Rendezvous.

hpevtMcRendezNoWakeup.name: hpevtMcRendezNoWakeup
hpevtMcRendezNoWakeup.description: The OS has not registered a wake-up mechanism for rendezvous.

hpevtMcRendezPalCantEscalate.name: hpevtMcRendezPalCantEscalate
hpevtMcRendezPalCantEscalate.description: PAL call failed to set the BINIT escalation bit

hpevtMcRendezPalGetFeatFail.name: hpevtMcRendezPalGetFeatFail
hpevtMcRendezPalGetFeatFail.description: The PAL call PAL_GET_FEATURES has failed.

hpevtMcRendezPalSetFeatFail.name: hpevtMcRendezPalSetFeatFail
hpevtMcRendezPalSetFeatFail.description: The PAL call PAL_SET_FEATURES has failed.

hpevtSalAbiFwError.name: hpevtSalAbiFwError
hpevtSalAbiFwError.description: An internal SAL_ABI firmware error was encountered. This is usually caused by a bad parameter passed to a function, corrupt memory, corrupt malloc, corrupt firmware tree or something similar. The data field contains the IP address of the function that encountered the error.

hpevtMemExtLoadOrdErr.name: hpevtMemExtLoadOrdErr
hpevtMemExtLoadOrdErr.description: The Memory extenders have not been loaded in the correct order.

hpevtEfiEsiTableLengthErr.name: hpevtEfiEsiTableLengthErr
hpevtEfiEsiTableLengthErr.description: The length field within the ESI (Extensible SAL Interface) table does not agree with the product of the entry_count field and the size of each entry. Data Field: computed value of the length based on entry_count and size of the entries.

hpevtEfiEsiTableChecksumErr.name: hpevtEfiEsiTableChecksumErr
hpevtEfiEsiTableChecksumErr.description: The computed checksum for the ESI (Extensible SAL Interface) table is not zero as expected. EFI is halting. Data Field: the computed checksum.

hpevtEfiEsiTableUnsupportedEntryType.name: hpevtEfiEsiTableUnsupportedEntryType
hpevtEfiEsiTableUnsupportedEntryType.description: EFI found an unsupported entry type within the ESI (Extensible SAL Interface) Table. Data Field: unknown type.

hpevtEfiGuidTooLarge.name: hpevtEfiGuidTooLarge
hpevtEfiGuidTooLarge.description: EFI was attempting to output a GUID in the EFI_GUID_HALF1 and EFI_GUID_HALF2 events which was larger than 128 bits. The data field contains the actual length of the GUID in bytes.

hpevtEfiHalt.name: hpevtEfiHalt
hpevtEfiHalt.description: EFI is halting. Look for the cause of the halt in preceding events. Data Field: the 'halt' (0x0F) major change in system state code.

hpevtMemChipspareNotSupported.name: hpevtMemChipspareNotSupported
hpevtMemChipspareNotSupported.description: This code will be sent when FW detects a rank installed in the system that doesn't support chipspare. The data field is used to indicate the rank that the x8 DIMMs are installed. It is in the format 0x00000000XDXCXBXA or 0x00000000YBYAXBXA where X and Y are the number of the rank.

hpevtEfiAssertError.name: hpevtEfiAssertError
hpevtEfiAssertError.description: EFI has detected an internal error. The actual error is unspecified by this event. Examine previous events and console output for possible explanations.

hpevtEfiEfiBreakpoint.name: hpevtEfiEfiBreakpoint
hpevtEfiEfiBreakpoint.description: EFI has executed the 'break' shell command. EFI is halting. The 'break' command is currently implemented as an infinite loop to halt EFI.

hpevtEfiHcdHostHung.name: hpevtEfiHcdHostHung
hpevtEfiHcdHostHung.description: The EFI USB interrupt service has detected the host controller is hung. EFI is halting.

hpevtEfiSalHandoffVerMismatch.name: hpevtEfiSalHandoffVerMismatch
hpevtEfiSalHandoffVerMismatch.description: The EFI/SAL handoff structure's version does not match EFI expectations. EFI is halting. Look for EFI_SAL_HANDOFF_VER_EXPECTED to provide EFI's expected value. Data Field: Actual value of the version in the structure.

hpevtEfiSalRtcServiceNotInit.name: hpevtEfiSalRtcServiceNotInit
hpevtEfiSalRtcServiceNotInit.description: EFI is unable to obtain access to all the RTC (Real Time Clock) SAL services. This means that EFI is unable to fully interact with the RTC. EFI is halting. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtEfiSalTimerServiceNotInit.name: hpevtEfiSalTimerServiceNotInit
hpevtEfiSalTimerServiceNotInit.description: EFI is unable to obtain access to all the SAL timer services. This means that EFI is unable to fully interact with the timer. EFI is halting. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtEfiSalStarttimerServiceNotInit.name: hpevtEfiSalStarttimerServiceNotInit
hpevtEfiSalStarttimerServiceNotInit.description: EFI is unable to start the periodic timer. This timer interrupts EFI periodically to process time sensitive events. EFI is halting. Data Field: Return status for internal EFI function.

hpevtEfiNoIoPortSpaceRegionFound.name: hpevtEfiNoIoPortSpaceRegionFound
hpevtEfiNoIoPortSpaceRegionFound.description: EFI did not find an I/O port space region in the MDT. EFI is halting.

hpevtEfiBreakpoint.name: hpevtEfiBreakpoint
hpevtEfiBreakpoint.description: EFI reached an unimplemented section of code. EFI is halting. Data Field: Unique identifier indicating the location reached within the code.

hpevtEfiSpeedyBootTokenNotRead.name: hpevtEfiSpeedyBootTokenNotRead
hpevtEfiSpeedyBootTokenNotRead.description: EFI was unable to read the current speedy boot settings. The speedy boot settings are stored within the BMC. EFI will use a default value of 0 and continue booting. The speedy boot functionality is also accessed via the boot test EFI shell command and via the OS. These other accesses will likely fail. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function..

hpevtEfiSalCallbackAttempted.name: hpevtEfiSalCallbackAttempted
hpevtEfiSalCallbackAttempted.description: A SAL Callback was attempted. This is not permitted. EFI is halting. Data Field: index of the function that was being called.

hpevtEfiSalFreqBaseUnknown.name: hpevtEfiSalFreqBaseUnknown
hpevtEfiSalFreqBaseUnknown.description: While attempting to calibrate the EFI stall timer, system firmware is unable to determine the frequency of the CPU interval timer. System firmware will assume 800 MHz for the purpose of the stall timer calibration and continue boot. Data Field: error status code (should be 0xFFFFFFFD).

hpevtEfiSysEventAlreadyInit.name: hpevtEfiSysEventAlreadyInit
hpevtEfiSysEventAlreadyInit.description: The EFI system events have already been initialized. This is unexpected. EFI is continuing. Data Field: the current value of the system event entry point.

hpevtEfiSysEventCreateEventFail.name: hpevtEfiSysEventCreateEventFail
hpevtEfiSysEventCreateEventFail.description: EFI was unable to create an internal virtualization event while initializing EFI's System Events (IPMI events). This internal event is not an IPMI event; rather it serves as a trigger for EFI to virtualize the System Event facility when going virtual. EFI will likely halt. Data Field: return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtFpgaNodeInitError.name: hpevtFpgaNodeInitError
hpevtFpgaNodeInitError.description: An error was detected while initializing the FPGA node and services associated with the PDH.

hpevtIoconfigNodeInitError.name: hpevtIoconfigNodeInitError
hpevtIoconfigNodeInitError.description: Firmware encountered an error when creating the ioconfig node as a child of the pdh node.

hpevtDillonPdhNodeInitError.name: hpevtDillonPdhNodeInitError
hpevtDillonPdhNodeInitError.description: System firmware was unable to correctly set up the pdh arbiter node as a child of the pdh node, or was unable to locate and attach the pdh arbiter service to the node. The status is returned in the data field.

hpevtPdhPropertyError.name: hpevtPdhPropertyError
hpevtPdhPropertyError.description: The PDH service was unable to either get or set the property specified in the data field as an ASCII message.

hpevtPdhAcpihwNodeError.name: hpevtPdhAcpihwNodeError
hpevtPdhAcpihwNodeError.description: PDH encountered an error creating the ACPI Hardware Node in the device tree or installing its properties.

hpevtPdhIpmiNodeError.name: hpevtPdhIpmiNodeError
hpevtPdhIpmiNodeError.description: The PDH service encountered an error while creating the ipmi node or adding properties to it. The status is in the data field.

hpevtBootCpusNotCompatible.name: hpevtBootCpusNotCompatible
hpevtBootCpusNotCompatible.description: Installed processors are not of compatible models or families

hpevtBootCacheSizesInconsistant.name: hpevtBootCacheSizesInconsistant
hpevtBootCacheSizesInconsistant.description: Processors with different cache sizes are installed

hpevtBootSelectingNewMonarch.name: hpevtBootSelectingNewMonarch
hpevtBootSelectingNewMonarch.description: SFW is selecting a new monarch processor due to compatibility problems.

hpevtBootMonSelSteppingsNoEqual.name: hpevtBootMonSelSteppingsNoEqual
hpevtBootMonSelSteppingsNoEqual.description: The monarch stepping is not equal to the lowest installed CPU stepping.

hpevtBootCpuOverClocked.name: hpevtBootCpuOverClocked
hpevtBootCpuOverClocked.description: A CPU's FSB frequency is overclocked. Data: Local CPU Number.

hpevtBootCpuInfoRomAccessError.name: hpevtBootCpuInfoRomAccessError
hpevtBootCpuInfoRomAccessError.description: There was an error reading the info ROM area of the CPU. Data: CPU Physical location

hpevtBootPalANotExecuted.name: hpevtBootPalANotExecuted
hpevtBootPalANotExecuted.description: PAL_A has not been executed and control has been transferred back to SAL_B.

hpevtBootPalBNotExecuted.name: hpevtBootPalBNotExecuted
hpevtBootPalBNotExecuted.description: PAL_B has not been executed and control has been transferred back to SAL_B.

hpevtBootProtoTypeCpuInstalled.name: hpevtBootProtoTypeCpuInstalled
hpevtBootProtoTypeCpuInstalled.description: Data: Lower 32 bits have Local CPU Number

hpevtCpuSupplementalTestFailed.name: hpevtCpuSupplementalTestFailed
hpevtCpuSupplementalTestFailed.description: Supplemental tests have been run on the cpus in the node and an error was encountered. If this event id is only emitted once, then the cpu detected that it failed on its own and the offending CPU id is in the data field. If the event is emitted three times, then the monarch CPU on the cell detected the error and the offending CPU id, expected data and actual data are reported in the data field of the three events.

hpevtFabricReadMbeError.name: hpevtFabricReadMbeError
hpevtFabricReadMbeError.description: While reading a XBC CSR, a multi-bit error was found. Data field includes the CSR data that includes the error. A previous event, FABRIC_READ_ERROR, details the CSR address that failed.

hpevtFabricUnexpectedStatus.name: hpevtFabricUnexpectedStatus
hpevtFabricUnexpectedStatus.description: The return value from a function was an unknown value. Data field is the unknown status that was returned.

hpevtEfiSysidBmcWarning.name: hpevtEfiSysidBmcWarning
hpevtEfiSysidBmcWarning.description: EFI queries the BMC on the system board for the status of a system ID. The BMC could not complete the request successfully or on time. Data Field: Internal EFI function status.

hpevtEfiSysidBmcReadError.name: hpevtEfiSysidBmcReadError
hpevtEfiSysidBmcReadError.description: BMC reported a system ID status as inaccessible, reported invalid status or cannot return the current value of a system ID. Data Field: uuid status or internal EFI function status. System ID status: a 1 byte value 0 extended to 64bits: 0x00 -> primary and secondary values are valid 0x01 -> primary and secondary values are magic 0x02 -> primary and secondary values are inaccessible 0x04 -> primary and secondary values are invalid 0x08 -> primary and secondary values are null (UUID only) 0x10 -> primary and secondary values are different, value (primary or secondary) is valid 0x11 -> primary and secondary values are different, value (primary or secondary) is magic 0x12 -> primary and secondary values are different, value (primary or secondary) is inaccessible 0x14 -> primary and secondary values are different, value (primary or secondary) is invalid 0x18 -> primary and secondary values are different, value (primary or secondary) is null (UUID only)

hpevtEfiSysidBmcWriteError.name: hpevtEfiSysidBmcWriteError
hpevtEfiSysidBmcWriteError.description: Firmware tried to write a primary or secondary system ID as requested by the user during the boot sequence. The write failed. Data Field: Internal EFI function status.

hpevtEfiSysidInvalid.name: hpevtEfiSysidInvalid
hpevtEfiSysidInvalid.description: The system ID(s) currently in the system is either invalid or, if the EFI_SYSID_BMC_WARNING, EFI_SYSID_BMC_READ_ERROR or EFI_SYSID_BMC_WRITE_ERROR events are also present, inaccessible to the system firmware. A stop boot condition will be generated and software license will probably be invalid. Data Field: 64-bit value. If preceded by 0xbad00000000000 the following valid values are possible: 0000 -> valid UUID (should never see this one) 0001 -> magic UUID 0002 -> inaccessible UUID 0004 -> invalid (bad CRC) UUID If zero, then one of the following conditions occurred: Invalid combination of primary and secondary system ID values User declined copying/entering system ID values when prompted by firmware All other values indicate failure during attempt to update system IDs.

hpevtEfiRtIvtEsiTableErr.name: hpevtEfiRtIvtEsiTableErr
hpevtEfiRtIvtEsiTableErr.description: EFI is unable to find the SAL services for installing interrupt handlers. EFI was trying to install the run-time handlers that are required for normal EFI booting. EFI will be halting. Data Field: internal EFI function status.

hpevtEfiRtIvtEsiQueryErr.name: hpevtEfiRtIvtEsiQueryErr
hpevtEfiRtIvtEsiQueryErr.description: EFI is unable to find the SAL service to install run-time interrupt handlers. These handlers are required for normal EFI booting. EFI will be halting. Data Field: internal EFI function status.

hpevtEfiBootIvtEsiTableErr.name: hpevtEfiBootIvtEsiTableErr
hpevtEfiBootIvtEsiTableErr.description: EFI is unable to find the SAL services for installing interrupt handlers. EFI was trying to install the boot-time handlers that are required for normal EFI booting. EFI will be halting. Data Field: internal EFI function status.

hpevtEfiBootIvtEsiQueryErr.name: hpevtEfiBootIvtEsiQueryErr
hpevtEfiBootIvtEsiQueryErr.description: EFI is unable to find the SAL service to install boot-time interrupt handlers. These handlers are required for normal EFI booting. EFI will be halting. Data Field: internal EFI function status.

hpevtUtilitiesParmListTooLarge.name: hpevtUtilitiesParmListTooLarge
hpevtUtilitiesParmListTooLarge.description: Too many parameters were passed in a request for the utilities system to perform an operation. No more data is provided.

hpevtXbcPortPresenceError.name: hpevtXbcPortPresenceError
hpevtXbcPortPresenceError.description: A crossbar port is expected to be present, but its presence detect bit is not set. Data field bits 32:43 contain the crossbar ID, bits 44:55 contain the port number for which the error occurred, and bits 0:31 contain the port status information.

hpevtXbcPortHwLinkError.name: hpevtXbcPortHwLinkError
hpevtXbcPortHwLinkError.description: A crossbar port is expected to have its HW_LINK_OK bit set, but it is not. Data field bits 32:43 contain the crossbar ID, bits 44:55 contain the port number for which the error occurred, and bits 0:31 contain the port status information.

hpevtXbcPortFeError.name: hpevtXbcPortFeError
hpevtXbcPortFeError.description: A connected crossbar port was found to have its FE bit set. Data field bits 32:43 contain the crossbar ID, bits 44:55 contain the port number for which the error occurred, and bits 0:31 contain the port status information.

hpevtXinLinkInitError.name: hpevtXinLinkInitError
hpevtXinLinkInitError.description: There was an error while initializing the Cell Controller-Xbc interface. The data field contains the address of the Cell Controller CSR for which the error occurred.

hpevtXinLinkInitFailed.name: hpevtXinLinkInitFailed
hpevtXinLinkInitFailed.description: The CC - XBC link failed to initialize.

hpevtEfiGetMfgModeNotInit.name: hpevtEfiGetMfgModeNotInit
hpevtEfiGetMfgModeNotInit.description: EFI is unable to determine current system mode. The EFI/SAL interface is not initialized. This interface should have been initialized before now. This event indicates an internal EFI error. EFI will continue executing.

hpevtEfiBmcMfgModeInvalid.name: hpevtEfiBmcMfgModeInvalid
hpevtEfiBmcMfgModeInvalid.description: The BMC has returned an invalid system mode. Data Field: the invalid mode. Expected values are 0 or 1.

hpevtEfiEnterMfgModeNotInit.name: hpevtEfiEnterMfgModeNotInit
hpevtEfiEnterMfgModeNotInit.description: EFI is unable to specify a new system mode. The EFI/SAL interface point is not initialized. This interface should have been initialized before now. This event indicates an internal EFI error. EFI will continue executing in the current mode.

hpevtEfiExitMfgModeNotInit.name: hpevtEfiExitMfgModeNotInit
hpevtEfiExitMfgModeNotInit.description: EFI is unable to enter normal system mode. The EFI/SAL interface is not initialized. This interface should have been initialized before now. This event indicates an internal EFI error. EFI will continue executing in the current mode.

hpevtEfiTaccessServiceNotInit.name: hpevtEfiTaccessServiceNotInit
hpevtEfiTaccessServiceNotInit.description: EFI is unable to initialize part of the SAL/EFI interface. This crucial service provides access to certain BMC functionality such as the security system. EFI will halt. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtTreeNodeNotFound.name: hpevtTreeNodeNotFound
hpevtTreeNodeNotFound.description: A needed tree node was not found. The data field contains the ASCII name of the tree node that was not found.

hpevtEfiSystemStateRunningErr.name: hpevtEfiSystemStateRunningErr
hpevtEfiSystemStateRunningErr.description: EFI is unable to modify the system state from 'booting' to 'running'. This is done as part of Exit Boot Services. The system will not be able to enter a sleep mode. Data Field: For errors, this data is zero. For warnings, this data indicates the current system state as: 0 Error 1 booting 2 running 3 attention 4 fault 5 booting + attention

hpevtPalBusConfigIncompatible.name: hpevtPalBusConfigIncompatible
hpevtPalBusConfigIncompatible.description: CPUBusConfigValue setting in options as been compared with what is reported by PAL as settable and CPUBusConfigValue is specifying at least one bit that is not supported by this version of PAL using the Get Processor Bus Dependent Configuration Features. This chassis code is emitted in pairs, the first data field contains the PAL expected values; the second data field contains the requested setting from options.

hpevtPalGetBusFeaturesFailed.name: hpevtPalGetBusFeaturesFailed
hpevtPalGetBusFeaturesFailed.description: Firmware was unable to correctly issue the Get Processor Bus Dependent Configuration Features command.

hpevtMemDimmPairMismatch.name: hpevtMemDimmPairMismatch
hpevtMemDimmPairMismatch.description: A pair of DIMMs installed in the system are mismatched, and that pair of DIMMs will not be used. The data field indicates which pair of DIMMs are mismatched in the format 0x000000000000XBXA where X is the number of the rank that is mismatched.

hpevtEfiPosseLibNotInit.name: hpevtEfiPosseLibNotInit
hpevtEfiPosseLibNotInit.description: EFI is unable to initialize internal library. This collection of internal services is required for much of EFI's functionality. EFI is halting.

hpevtEfiSecurityNotInit.name: hpevtEfiSecurityNotInit
hpevtEfiSecurityNotInit.description: EFI is unable to initialize the security level. The privilege level of the system may or may not be Admin. It is likely certain EFI facilities will be unavailable. EFI will continue booting but security may be compromised. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtEfiSecInvalidSysmode.name: hpevtEfiSecInvalidSysmode
hpevtEfiSecInvalidSysmode.description: EFI detected an invalid value for its internal privilege level. This value is stored within SAL. EFI will continue but system security may be compromised. Data Field: The invalid privilege level.

hpevtEfiSecSetPassLevelErr.name: hpevtEfiSecSetPassLevelErr
hpevtEfiSecSetPassLevelErr.description: EFI detected an invalid privilege level when setting a BMC password. Only the levels of Admin (0x30) and User (0x20) are permitted. Data Field: the invalid privilege level.

hpevtMdtBad.name: hpevtMdtBad
hpevtMdtBad.description: SFW has determined that the Memory Data Table (MDT) table is invalid.

hpevtBootCpuBadCoreFixedRatio.name: hpevtBootCpuBadCoreFixedRatio
hpevtBootCpuBadCoreFixedRatio.description: Processor has incompatible fixed core ratio. Data: Local CPU Number.

hpevtBootAllCpusSlatedForCompatDeconfig.name: hpevtBootAllCpusSlatedForCompatDeconfig
hpevtBootAllCpusSlatedForCompatDeconfig.description: Data: A bitmask for which CPUs are slated to be deconfigured

hpevtXbcReadRemoteRouteError.name: hpevtXbcReadRemoteRouteError
hpevtXbcReadRemoteRouteError.description: An error occurred while reading a crossbar remote route table, or an unexpected/invalid value was read from the table. The data field consists of the crossbar ID (32:43), the port number of which the table was read (44:55), and the return status of the read call (0:32).

hpevtXbcReadNeighborInfoError.name: hpevtXbcReadNeighborInfoError
hpevtXbcReadNeighborInfoError.description: An error occurred while trying to read the PORT[n]_NEIGHBOR_INFO crossbar CSR. The data field consists of the crossbar ID (32:43) and port number (44:55) for which the CSR was read.

hpevtMemDimmQuadMismatch.name: hpevtMemDimmQuadMismatch
hpevtMemDimmQuadMismatch.description: A quad of DIMMs installed in the system are mismatched, and that quad of DIMMs will not be used. The data field indicates which quad of DIMMs are mismatched in the format 0x00000000XDXCXBXA where X is the number of the rank that is mismatched.

hpevtMemDimmFailed.name: hpevtMemDimmFailed
hpevtMemDimmFailed.description: The DIMM at the physical location given by the data field had excessive errors and has been marked as 'FAILED' by firmware.

hpevtXbcPortOeError.name: hpevtXbcPortOeError
hpevtXbcPortOeError.description: A XBC port was expected to be functional, but its OE bit was not set. The data field consists of the contents of the port_status CSR (0:31), the XBC number (32:43), and the port number (44:55).

hpevtXbcPortStatusError.name: hpevtXbcPortStatusError
hpevtXbcPortStatusError.description: Unable to read the PORT_STATUS CSR for a XBC port. The data field consists of the contents of the PORT_STATUS CSR (0:31), the XBC number (32:43), and the port number (44:55).

hpevtXbcPortLandmined.name: hpevtXbcPortLandmined
