hpevtXbcPortLandmined.description: A XBC port was unexpectedly found to be landmined. The data field consists of the XBC number (32:43) and the port number (44:55).

hpevtPdIncompatibleCpuSpeeds.name: hpevtPdIncompatibleCpuSpeeds
hpevtPdIncompatibleCpuSpeeds.description: Reporting cell tried to rendezvous with a cell with processors that are running at a different speed. The data field lists the offending cell

hpevtFabricCellLinkNotInit.name: hpevtFabricCellLinkNotInit
hpevtFabricCellLinkNotInit.description: The link between the local CC and the local XBC is unexpectedly not initialized. The data field is the XIN_LINK_STATE CC CSR value.

hpevtFabricInvalidXbcNum.name: hpevtFabricInvalidXbcNum
hpevtFabricInvalidXbcNum.description: A value that was expected to be a XBC number was found to be an invalid XBC number. The data field is the invalid XBC number.

hpevtFabricInvalidXbcPortNum.name: hpevtFabricInvalidXbcPortNum
hpevtFabricInvalidXbcPortNum.description: A value that was expected to be a valid XBC port number was found to be invalid. The data field is the XBC number (33:44) and the invalid XBC port number (44:55).

hpevtUtilitiesLedParamError.name: hpevtUtilitiesLedParamError
hpevtUtilitiesLedParamError.description: A bad parameter was passed to the utilities function that manipulates the LED on replaceable parts. The offending parameter is displayed in the data field.

hpevtFabricUnexpectedNtype.name: hpevtFabricUnexpectedNtype
hpevtFabricUnexpectedNtype.description: A neighbor type read from a XBC PORT_NEIGHBOR_INFO CSR was different than the expected neighbor type. This event is emitted twice, first with expected data and second with actual data. Data field 1: XBC number (43:32), XBC port number (55:44), expected type (31:0) Data field 2: XBC number (43:32), XBC port number (55:44), actual neighbor type (31:0).

hpevtFabricPortNotCc.name: hpevtFabricPortNotCc
hpevtFabricPortNotCc.description: A XBC port number was unexpectedly found to not be a valid XBC-CC port. The data field consists of the XBC number (32:43) and the port number (44:55).

hpevtFabricPortNotXbc.name: hpevtFabricPortNotXbc
hpevtFabricPortNotXbc.description: A XBC port was unexpectedly found to be an invalid XBC-XBC port. The data field consists of the XBC number (32:43) and the port number (44:55).

hpevtFabricUnexpectedNChip.name: hpevtFabricUnexpectedNChip
hpevtFabricUnexpectedNChip.description: The XBC neighbor chip number does not match the expected value for this topology. The data field contains the expected neighbor chip number (32:63) and the actual neighbor chip number (0:31).

hpevtFabricUnexpectedNPort.name: hpevtFabricUnexpectedNPort
hpevtFabricUnexpectedNPort.description: The XBC neighbor port number does not match the expected value for this topology. The data field contains the expected neighbor port number (32:63) and the actual neighbor port number (0:31).

hpevtBootNvmWriteToBmcTokenFailure.name: hpevtBootNvmWriteToBmcTokenFailure
hpevtBootNvmWriteToBmcTokenFailure.description: A write to a BMC token has failed. This is a boot warning condition. Data: Upper 32 bits, BMC failure return code. Lower 32 bits, BMC token number that failed.

hpevtUtilitiesLedError.name: hpevtUtilitiesLedError
hpevtUtilitiesLedError.description: The utilities system reported an error while trying to carry out the command to turn on, flash or turn off the LED. The status returned by the command is displayed in the data field.

hpevtDuplicateCpuIds.name: hpevtDuplicateCpuIds
hpevtDuplicateCpuIds.description: 2 cpus think that they have the same ID within the cell. Typically this would mean that PAL reported the same cpu id for more than 1 cpu on a bus. The cpuid is in the data field.

hpevtHp_uxHexFaultCode.name: hpevtHp_uxHexFaultCode
hpevtHp_uxHexFaultCode.description: OS legacy PA hex fault code (Bxxx). Possible I/O error or system panic

hpevtHp_uxDumpStatus.name: hpevtHp_uxDumpStatus
hpevtHp_uxDumpStatus.description: A memory dump occurred on the system, or on one partition in a cellular system. The dump occurred due to either a non-recoverable error or by user request. EFxx is the OS dump status (the success/failure of the writing of the dump). EF00 = success (followed by either EF0A = successful dump with sync, or EF09 = successful dump without sync), EFFF = a general error, EFFE = dump path assertion failure, EFFD = no dump was taken by default, choice or failure, EFFC = dump was aborted by user.

hpevtSettingProcTimeoutFail.name: hpevtSettingProcTimeoutFail
hpevtSettingProcTimeoutFail.description: SFW has failed to set the processor timeout value via a PAL call. Data: PAL call return value.

hpevtEfiSecInitVerifyErr.name: hpevtEfiSecInitVerifyErr
hpevtEfiSecInitVerifyErr.description: During EFI security initialization, the attempt to determine what privilege level a blank password provides, failed. Most likely this indicates the BMC has failed. EFI assumes that the BMC has failed and will attempt to continue booting. Some EFI functionality may be unavailable. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtEfiSecInitCloseErr.name: hpevtEfiSecInitCloseErr
hpevtEfiSecInitCloseErr.description: As part of normal security initialization, EFI attempted to issue a close session to the BMC (I.e. force the BMC to GUEST mode). This attempt failed. EFI is unable to initialize the security system. EFI will continue but security may be compromised. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtEfiSecInitOpenErr.name: hpevtEfiSecInitOpenErr
hpevtEfiSecInitOpenErr.description: As part of normal security initialization, EFI attempted to issue an open session to the BMC in order to raise the privilege level to the highest permitted by a blank password. This attempt failed. EFI is unable to initialize the security system. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtEfiSecInitWriteErr.name: hpevtEfiSecInitWriteErr
hpevtEfiSecInitWriteErr.description: As part of normal security initialization, EFI attempted to record the current privilege level. This attempt failed. EFI is unable to initialize the security system. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtEfiSecInitWriteDenied.name: hpevtEfiSecInitWriteDenied
hpevtEfiSecInitWriteDenied.description: As part of normal security initialization, EFI attempted to record the current privilege level. This attempt failed with a privilege violation error. EFI is unable to initialize the security system. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtHp_uxDumpWriteError.name: hpevtHp_uxDumpWriteError
hpevtHp_uxDumpWriteError.description: OS dump, error writing image area to disk (E055)

hpevtErrDeadlockResetDetected.name: hpevtErrDeadlockResetDetected
hpevtErrDeadlockResetDetected.description: Early in bootstrap, the coherency controller (CC) registers are checked for Deadlock Recovery Reset. This chassis code indicates that CC logs will be stored to NVRAM.

hpevtMemParityErr.name: hpevtMemParityErr
hpevtMemParityErr.description: SFW detected a memory address parity error. The data field contains the physical location of DIMM that saw the parity error.

hpevtMemDimmLoadOrdErr.name: hpevtMemDimmLoadOrdErr
hpevtMemDimmLoadOrdErr.description: The loading order of the DIMMs is incorrect. The cell is halted.

hpevtMemRefreshStartError.name: hpevtMemRefreshStartError
hpevtMemRefreshStartError.description: Timeout Waiting for SDRAM parts to become ready - mem_status[0] Refresh Control Register

hpevtMemExtBaseboardIncompatible.name: hpevtMemExtBaseboardIncompatible
hpevtMemExtBaseboardIncompatible.description: The version of Memory extender installed in the system has not been qualified to work with the version of the baseboard installed in the system.

hpevtFabricDifferentTopologies.name: hpevtFabricDifferentTopologies
hpevtFabricDifferentTopologies.description: There is a fabric topology mismatch with the XBCs in the complex. Data Field: (Topology of XBC << 32) | Topology of destination XBC 0x00 Topology not yet determined 0x30 Domelight 0x40 U-Turn (Left cabinet) 0x41 U-Turn (Right cabinet) 0x42 Cross-Flex 0x43 U-Turn

hpevtFabricInvalidXbc2XbcPort.name: hpevtFabricInvalidXbc2XbcPort
hpevtFabricInvalidXbc2XbcPort.description: While routing the XBC to XBC ports, an invalid port was encountered. The data field is the crossbar number (32:43) and the port number (44:55).

hpevtFabricGetNeighborInfoError.name: hpevtFabricGetNeighborInfoError
hpevtFabricGetNeighborInfoError.description: The XBC could not get neighbor information. Data Field: XBC # << 32 | internal port attempting to access neighbor

hpevtXbcRoutingErrorState.name: hpevtXbcRoutingErrorState
hpevtXbcRoutingErrorState.description: For the XBC being routed, routing has already been attempted, but an error occurred. Inspect chassis codes from other cells for more details regarding the nature of the problem. The data field consists of the XBC number (32:63)

hpevtNoNvmErrLogSpace.name: hpevtNoNvmErrLogSpace
hpevtNoNvmErrLogSpace.description: This means that the error event log cannot be logged to the persistent storage. The data field gives the event type that was supposed to be logged.

hpevtXbcPortError.name: hpevtXbcPortError
hpevtXbcPortError.description: An XBC port was found to have an unexpected error. The data field consists of the crossbar number (32:63) and the current port errors (0:31)

hpevtXbcPortRouteAround.name: hpevtXbcPortRouteAround
hpevtXbcPortRouteAround.description: During fabric routing a port on a XBC was found in error or had been previously marked as in error. PDC will route around this XBC port. Data Field: XBC number (32:63) and external XBC port number (0:31)

hpevtXbcUnexpectedState.name: hpevtXbcUnexpectedState
hpevtXbcUnexpectedState.description: Data field: the unexpected forward progress state (0:31) XBC number (32:44) Cell number (56:63)

hpevtXbcRoutingStateTimeout.name: hpevtXbcRoutingStateTimeout
hpevtXbcRoutingStateTimeout.description: A crossbar was found to be in an unexpected forward progress state during fabric routing. This crossbar stayed in the unexpected state until Fabric Discovery timed out. Data field: unexpected forward progress (0:31) XBC number (32:44) Cell number (56:63)

hpevtXbcNeighborPortNotRoutable.name: hpevtXbcNeighborPortNotRoutable
hpevtXbcNeighborPortNotRoutable.description: An XBC port was found that is not healthy. This indicates at least one of the following about the port: - Hardware link is not okay - Presence detect is false - Fatal error detected - SBE detected - LPE detected - Port landmined The data field of the chassis code indicates which port is unhealthy, as well as the fabric routing state before the problem was encountered.

hpevtFabricCcToXbcError.name: hpevtFabricCcToXbcError
hpevtFabricCcToXbcError.description: The CC to XBC link is not viable.

hpevtFabricRouteXbcError.name: hpevtFabricRouteXbcError
hpevtFabricRouteXbcError.description: There was a problem performing remote routing on the local XBC. Chassis codes sent before this one may provide more details about the exact nature of the problem. The data field consists of the XBC number that failed routing (32:63)

hpevtFabricMaxBrokenLinks.name: hpevtFabricMaxBrokenLinks
hpevtFabricMaxBrokenLinks.description: Two or more XBC-XBC links were found to be broken. The data field is the XBC number (32:63) and a bit map of the ports broken (0:31)

hpevtXbcSemaphoreTakeoverFailed.name: hpevtXbcSemaphoreTakeoverFailed
hpevtXbcSemaphoreTakeoverFailed.description: After unlocking the XBC Global Semaphore for a takeover, this cell did not get the semaphore.

hpevtXbcForceUnlockSm4Timeout.name: hpevtXbcForceUnlockSm4Timeout
hpevtXbcForceUnlockSm4Timeout.description: When a cell holds an XBC semaphore for an extended period of time, fabric will attempt to takeover the semaphore so that the rest of the cells will have access to it. Fabric will attempt to take the SM4 for a period of time. If it is unable to unlock the SM4 within the timeout period, it will send this chassis code and halt the cell. Data field: XBC number (32:63) and current owner (cell) of the semaphore (0:31)

hpevtXbcGetGlobalSm4Timeout.name: hpevtXbcGetGlobalSm4Timeout
hpevtXbcGetGlobalSm4Timeout.description: During Fabric Discovery, the cell will wait until it gets the XBC's Global Semaphore. It waits for a very long time. This chassis code indicates that the wait has timed out.

hpevtXbcReleaseSm4Timeout.name: hpevtXbcReleaseSm4Timeout
hpevtXbcReleaseSm4Timeout.description: The XBC Release Semaphore timeout is designed to fail last. The semaphore could not be released. Any other cell (even outside the PD) may be blocked because the XBC is a global resource. Data field: current semaphore owner (0:31) XBC number (32:43) port number (44:55) cell number (56:63)

hpevtMpBatteryFailure.name: hpevtMpBatteryFailure
hpevtMpBatteryFailure.description: Management Processor Firmware detected improper data in NVRAM (bad checksums.) Either the NVRAM layout changed, or the Management Processor Battery may not be maintaining the data through A/C power cycles.

hpevtMpSoftwareError.name: hpevtMpSoftwareError
hpevtMpSoftwareError.description: Management Processor Firmware detected a software error and is logging an event. The data represents data associated with the error seen.

hpevtMpI2cCommError.name: hpevtMpI2cCommError
hpevtMpI2cCommError.description: An I2C Communication failure with the Baseboard Management Controller was detected. Without I2C communication, the system cannot be powered on/off or reset.

hpevtRomCrcError.name: hpevtRomCrcError
hpevtRomCrcError.description: A stored CRC value did not match the calculated CRC value for the specified address.

hpevtCpuRevisionMismatch.name: hpevtCpuRevisionMismatch
hpevtCpuRevisionMismatch.description: 2 cpus in the system are reporting different revisions. This event will be emitted in groups of 3 with the two revisions reported in the first 2 data fields and the cpu number in the 3rd data field.

hpevtCpuFreqMismatch.name: hpevtCpuFreqMismatch
hpevtCpuFreqMismatch.description: This chassis code will be emitted in pairs. 2 cpus are reporting that they are running at different frequencies. The two frequencies are reported in the data fields.

hpevtCpuOverclocked.name: hpevtCpuOverclocked
hpevtCpuOverclocked.description: The rating for the cpu and the actual speed will be emitted in 2 sequential event data fields.

hpevtCmplxProfilIncoherent.name: hpevtCmplxProfilIncoherent
hpevtCmplxProfilIncoherent.description: The complex profile is stored in NVRAM on the MP and each cell. All copies must match. For this error to be generated, not only is the MP's copy of the complex profile invalid, but not all of the cell's copies match.

hpevtDuplicateCabinet.name: hpevtDuplicateCabinet
hpevtDuplicateCabinet.description: The MP detected 2 or more cabinets with the same cabinet number.

hpevtIdCommandRequired.name: hpevtIdCommandRequired
hpevtIdCommandRequired.description: The complex identification information in group A of the complex profile is invalid. The MP (Manageability Processor) command 'ID' must be run. The SSKEY hardware is required.

hpevtNvramBatteryFail.name: hpevtNvramBatteryFail
hpevtNvramBatteryFail.description: The battery on the SBCH is below the safe threshold. The battery can be replaced online.

hpevtPartitionTimeoutReset.name: hpevtPartitionTimeoutReset
hpevtPartitionTimeoutReset.description: The partition is being reset because its watchdog timer expired and automatic restart is enabled.

hpevtPdhcWatchdogTimedOut.name: hpevtPdhcWatchdogTimedOut
hpevtPdhcWatchdogTimedOut.description: The processor dependent hardware controller (PDHC) on the cell board had its watchdog timer expire. The PDHC will reset the watchdog as the main program runs. If the watchdog does not get reset within 7 seconds the timer will expire, resetting the PDHC.

hpevtAbortPowerupOth.name: hpevtAbortPowerupOth
hpevtAbortPowerupOth.description: The Cabinet Power Up request was aborted due to ambient air over temperature.

hpevtAbortPwrupBps.name: hpevtAbortPwrupBps
hpevtAbortPwrupBps.description: The power requirements for the cabinet exceeds the capabilities of the available Bulk Power Supplies. The PM3 section of the Utilities Subsystems keeps a tally of the power requirements for all installed entities in a cabinet. The power available from the Bulk Power Supplies does not meet the requirements of the installed entities, according to the Cabinet Power Tally.

hpevtAbortStartBlowr.name: hpevtAbortStartBlowr
hpevtAbortStartBlowr.description: When given a power up request, the cabinet had to abort the start up due to less than the required number of Cabinet Blowers installed.

hpevtAbortStartIofan.name: hpevtAbortStartIofan
hpevtAbortStartIofan.description: When given a power up request, the cabinet had to abort the start up due to less than the required number of IO fans present.

hpevtAcDeleted.name: hpevtAcDeleted
hpevtAcDeleted.description: The AC power connected to the PDCA (Power Distribution Control Assembly) was removed. The data field contains the physical location of the PDCA. The PDCA source that was deleted can be identified by the implementation dependent field (data byte 3) of the physical location: data byte[3]: 0 for PDCA 0, 1 for PDCA 1.

hpevtBlowrFail.name: hpevtBlowrFail
hpevtBlowrFail.description: A cabinet main blower has failed. Depending on the number of blowers still operating, the cabinet may or may not shut down. View the Error Log entries to determine if the cabinet is operating. If many log entries call out entities powering off during the same time frame as this BLOWR_FAIL, the cabinet has probably shutdown. Carefully review the log for the first few events within the same time frame for the root cause of the problem. The GSP command, PS, will show a detailed power status for a cabinet. If the +48V LED on the Front Panel Board is not lit, power is not enabled to the cabinet. This is an indication the cabinet blowers have probably gone from N to N - 1 status requiring an immediate cabinet shutdown.

hpevtBpsFail48flt.name: hpevtBpsFail48flt
hpevtBpsFail48flt.description: A 48 Volt DC Converter powered by the specified PDCA failed on the designated Bulk Power Supply. The PDCA powering the converter on the BPS that failed can be identified by the implementation dependent field (data byte 3) of the BPS' physical location: data byte[3]: 0 for PDCA 0, 1 for PDCA 1.

hpevtBpsFailFanflt.name: hpevtBpsFailFanflt
hpevtBpsFailFanflt.description: The designated Bulk Power Supply is reporting its fan has failed.

hpevtBpsFailOt.name: hpevtBpsFailOt
hpevtBpsFailOt.description: The 48 Volt DC Converter powered by the specified PDCA in the designated Bulk Power Supply, is in over temp condition. The PDCA powering the converter on the BPS that failed can be identified by the activity status (last byte of chassis code): e = PDCA 1 f = PDCA 0

hpevtBpsNotRedundant.name: hpevtBpsNotRedundant
hpevtBpsNotRedundant.description: The number of functioning Bulk Power Supplies has decreased to where the Cabinet Power supplied (number of available Bulk Power Supplies times power output per each) minus the estimated Cabinet Power consumed is greater than 0, but less than the output of one Bulk Power Supply.

hpevtBpsOvervoltage.name: hpevtBpsOvervoltage
hpevtBpsOvervoltage.description: The PM has detected the value of +48V power, as measured on the UGUY board, has exceeded an upper threshold.

hpevtBpsUndervoltage.name: hpevtBpsUndervoltage
hpevtBpsUndervoltage.description: The PM has detected the value of +48V power, as measured on the UGUY board, has fallen below a lower threshold.

hpevtCabFanFail.name: hpevtCabFanFail
hpevtCabFanFail.description: A cabinet fan has failed. Depending on the number of cabinet fans still operating, the cabinet may or may not shut down. View the Error Log entries to determine if the cabinet is operating.

hpevtHkpOvervoltage.name: hpevtHkpOvervoltage
hpevtHkpOvervoltage.description: Housekeeping power has exceeded expected levels.

hpevtHkpUndervoltage.name: hpevtHkpUndervoltage
hpevtHkpUndervoltage.description: Housekeeping power has fallen below expected levels.

hpevtIllegalBpsCfgOrPhaseFlt.name: hpevtIllegalBpsCfgOrPhaseFlt
hpevtIllegalBpsCfgOrPhaseFlt.description: Through failures or reconfiguration, the BPS for the cabinet named are illegally configured. There must be a BPS connected to each phase of the power. Phase 1 feeds BPS slots 0 & 1, phase 2 feeds slots 2 & 3, and phase 3 feeds 4 & 5. There must be a BPS connected to each phase. If 4 BPS are installed in a cabinet in slots 0 - 3 and 4 & 5 were empty, this would be an illegal configuration. They should be installed in 0,1,2,and 4 or 0,1,3,and 5 or some combination thereof. The PDCA physical location determines which phase is configured incorrectly. Data Byte 3 (implementation dependent field) indicates the PDCA number used when the configuration error occurred:

hpevtIllegalBpsid.name: hpevtIllegalBpsid
hpevtIllegalBpsid.description: A Bulk Power Supply is reporting an unknown BPS ID. The Bulk Power Supply will not be powered up and added to the Power Available tally. If cabinet is not powered up, it will refuse to power up until this fault is corrected.

hpevtInletOvertempHi.name: hpevtInletOvertempHi
hpevtInletOvertempHi.description: The cabinet's Ambient Air Sensor detected a change in air temperature entering the over-temp-high range. The Cabinet will be shutting itself down to prevent component damage.

hpevtInletOvertempLo.name: hpevtInletOvertempLo
hpevtInletOvertempLo.description: The cabinet's Ambient Air Sensor detected a change in air temperature crossing to the low range. The air temperature may be rising or falling. This is just a reporting of entering the over-temp-low range.

hpevtInletOvertempMid.name: hpevtInletOvertempMid
hpevtInletOvertempMid.description: The cabinet's Ambient Air Sensor detected a change in air temperature crossing to the mid range. The air temperature may be rising or falling. This is just a reporting of entering the over-temp-mid range..

hpevtIofanFail.name: hpevtIofanFail
hpevtIofanFail.description: An IO Chassis cooling fan has failed. Depending on the number of fans still operating, the cabinet may or may not shut down. View Error Log entries to determine if the cabinet is operating. If many log entries call out entities powering off during the same time frame as this IOFAN_FAIL, the cabinet has probably shutdown. Carefully review the log for the first few events within the same time frame for the root cause of the problem. The Guardian Service Processor command, PS, will show a detailed power status for a cabinet. The +48V LED on the Front Panel Board not lit, power is not enabled to the cabinet, indicating the cabinet IO Chassis fans have probably gone from N to N - 1 status requiring an immediate cabinet shutdown.

hpevtPowerOverload.name: hpevtPowerOverload
hpevtPowerOverload.description: This code is issued when the Cabinet Power supplied (number of Bulk Power Supplies times power output per each) minus the estimated Cabinet Power consumed drops below 0. Utilities firmware will not allow a cabinet in this state to power up (see ABORT_PWRUP_BPS). Utilities firmware will not shut down a cabinet in this state. However, there is a possibility of a cabinet brownout, making the cabinet unreliable.

hpevtShutdownBlowr.name: hpevtShutdownBlowr
hpevtShutdownBlowr.description: After a BLOWR_FAIL, there were N-1 blowers functioning. This is an illegal condition causing immediate cabinet shutdown to prevent component damage.

hpevtShutdownIofan.name: hpevtShutdownIofan
hpevtShutdownIofan.description: After a IOFAN_FAIL, there were N-1 fans functioning. This is an illegal condition causing immediate cabinet shutdown to prevent component damage.

hpevtXucFanFail.name: hpevtXucFanFail
hpevtXucFanFail.description: One of two fans in the Utility chassis of the IO Expansion Cabinet has failed.

hpevtCluWatchdogReset.name: hpevtCluWatchdogReset
hpevtCluWatchdogReset.description: The Watchdog Timer checks for inactivity, or hung state, of the Cabinet Level Utilities (CLU) portion of the UGUY. During activity, the timer is continually reset. If the timer expires, it will automatically reset the CLU microprocessor. This will not affect running partitions.

hpevtEepromInvalidCksm.name: hpevtEepromInvalidCksm
hpevtEepromInvalidCksm.description: An invalid checksum was received when reading the FRUID EEPROM for the device named in the chassis code. If this is a single error, the fault lies with the named FRU. If there are many INVALID_CKSM entries in the Event Log, there is probably a problem with the I2C bus.

hpevtHbpbBoardPowerFault.name: hpevtHbpbBoardPowerFault
hpevtHbpbBoardPowerFault.description: One or more of the System Backplane Power Boards is reporting a DC Fault through the System Backplane Local Power Monitor. The physical location of the failing power board is in the Data Field of the event.

hpevtHiobEepromRdFail.name: hpevtHiobEepromRdFail
hpevtHiobEepromRdFail.description: An attempt to read the EEPROM (FRUID) on the IO Backplane Board failed.

hpevtHiopbEepromRdFail.name: hpevtHiopbEepromRdFail
hpevtHiopbEepromRdFail.description: An attempt to read the EEPROM (FRUID) on the IO Backplane Power Board failed.

hpevtHiopbLpmFltRdFail.name: hpevtHiopbLpmFltRdFail
hpevtHiopbLpmFltRdFail.description: An attempt to read the Local Power Monitor Fault register on the IO Backplane Power Board failed.

hpevtHiopbOvertemp.name: hpevtHiopbOvertemp
hpevtHiopbOvertemp.description: The Local Power Monitor of the named IO Chassis is reporting a Power Brick over temperature condition.

hpevtHiopbPowerFault.name: hpevtHiopbPowerFault
hpevtHiopbPowerFault.description: The Local Power Monitor on the named IO Chassis has reported a power fault condition.

hpevtHiopbVoltMrgnFail.name: hpevtHiopbVoltMrgnFail
hpevtHiopbVoltMrgnFail.description: The Local Power Monitor on the named IO Power Board failed to properly margin the power as commanded.

hpevtSbchEepromRdFail.name: hpevtSbchEepromRdFail
hpevtSbchEepromRdFail.description: Either by command or as part of initialization, the data from a FRUID EEPROM failed a read command. This does not necessarily mean the FRU has failed, just that the FRUID data cannot be read.

hpevtUguyEepromRdFail.name: hpevtUguyEepromRdFail
hpevtUguyEepromRdFail.description: Either by command or as part of initialization, the data from a FRUID EEPROM failed a read command. This does not necessarily mean the FRU has failed, just that the FRUID can't be read.

hpevtSysBkpEepromRdFail.name: hpevtSysBkpEepromRdFail
hpevtSysBkpEepromRdFail.description: An attempt to read the EEPROM (FRUID) on the System Backplane failed

hpevtSysBkpI2cRdFail.name: hpevtSysBkpI2cRdFail
hpevtSysBkpI2cRdFail.description: A read command on the system backplane I2C bus failed.

hpevtSysBkpI2cWrFail.name: hpevtSysBkpI2cWrFail
hpevtSysBkpI2cWrFail.description: A write command on the system backplane I2C bus failed. The type of command that failed can be identified by the activity status field (last byte) of the encoded field. B = RC Cable Configuration Register write C = Backplane Voltage Margin Register write 9 = Flex circuit configuration register write

hpevtSysBkpPowerFault.name: hpevtSysBkpPowerFault
hpevtSysBkpPowerFault.description: The Local Power Monitor on the named System Backplane has detected a power fault. The failing Backplane Power Board status is read from the Backplane LPM I2C interface register and the value is placed in the data field of the event (bits 15-8).

hpevtSysBkpVoltMrgnFail.name: hpevtSysBkpVoltMrgnFail
hpevtSysBkpVoltMrgnFail.description: Margining voltage to the System Backplane has failed.

hpevtWriteFruDataFail.name: hpevtWriteFruDataFail
hpevtWriteFruDataFail.description: An attempt to write data to the FRUID EEPROM by the MFG level MP command WF failed. The FRU handle of the failing FRUID is embedded in the two uppermost bytes of the data field.

hpevtCpuFanFail.name: hpevtCpuFanFail
hpevtCpuFanFail.description: The fan on a CPU is not operating in a manner that provides enough air flow to cool the processor

hpevtCpuFanSlow.name: hpevtCpuFanSlow
hpevtCpuFanSlow.description: The fan on a CPU is operating in a manner that provides enough air flow to cool the processor but is not at normal operation

hpevtDnaFanFail.name: hpevtDnaFanFail
hpevtDnaFanFail.description: The fan on a CC chip is not operating in a manner that provides enough air flow to cool the processor

hpevtDnaFanSlow.name: hpevtDnaFanSlow
hpevtDnaFanSlow.description: The fan on a CC chip is operating in a manner that provides enough air flow to cool the processor but is not at normal operation

hpevtPdhcToSysfwRevMismtch.name: hpevtPdhcToSysfwRevMismtch
hpevtPdhcToSysfwRevMismtch.description: System FW and the PDHC have incompatible shared memory interface revisions. Data byte 0 is the PDHC's supported ICM revision number. Data byte 1 is System FW's supported ICM revision number.

hpevtPdhCtrlrFwMismatch.name: hpevtPdhCtrlrFwMismatch
hpevtPdhCtrlrFwMismatch.description: The MP checked the FW revision of the PDHC identified in the physical location data field and discovered that it did not recognize the revision as one that it has been qualed with. This is an unsupported configuration.

hpevtCellPowerFault.name: hpevtCellPowerFault
hpevtCellPowerFault.description: The local Power Monitor is reporting a fault with the named Cell Power Board. The data field of this event can be decoded as follows where a bit set in any of the status fields indicates a fault: data byte 0: (power_good << 1) | (power_fault) data byte 1: Cell Power Board converters status bits[0:2] - memory power bricks 0-2 status bits[3:5] - power i/f bus bricks 0-2 status bits[6:7] - JAB core power bricks 0-1 status data byte 2: Cell converters status bit 0 - clock power status bit 1 - cache power status bit 2 - link power status bit 3 - CC core power status bit 4 - FSB power status bit 5 - 48-V status data byte 3: CPU module converters status bit 0 - CPU module 0 core power status bit 2 - CPU module 1 core power status bit 4 - CPU module 2 core power status bit 6 - CPU module 3 core power status

hpevtCpuInitNodeError.name: hpevtCpuInitNodeError
hpevtCpuInitNodeError.description: The CPU node retuned an error when calling its initialize node function. The specific status is displayed in the data field.

hpevtCpuExecuteCmdError.name: hpevtCpuExecuteCmdError
hpevtCpuExecuteCmdError.description: ExecuteCommand issues commands that execute on remote CPUs via IPI interrupts. If the command failed to execute, this event is printed and the data field contains the status.

hpevtCpuCmdStateInvalid.name: hpevtCpuCmdStateInvalid
hpevtCpuCmdStateInvalid.description: A remote CPU is in a state where it cannot receive and execute a new command. The current status of the CPU is provided in the data field.

hpevtCpuPalProcError.name: hpevtCpuPalProcError
hpevtCpuPalProcError.description: An error was encountered when executing a PAL_PROC. This code will be emitted in pairs. The Proc INDEX will be in the data of the first chassis code. The status is in the second data field.

hpevtBootCpuLoadingError.name: hpevtBootCpuLoadingError
hpevtBootCpuLoadingError.description: CPUs not loaded in correct order. Correct loading order is CPU 0, 1, 2, 3.

hpevtXbcPersistantError.name: hpevtXbcPersistantError
hpevtXbcPersistantError.description: The XBC logged a SBE or LPE after they should have been cleared. Either the clear failed, or a new error was logged immediately. Data field: XBC number (32:43), port number (44:55), port status information (0:31)

hpevtXbcLinkTestError.name: hpevtXbcLinkTestError
hpevtXbcLinkTestError.description: The CC to XBC Link pattern test failed. Data Field: This event will be emitted three times 1st event: XBC number (32:43), port number (44:55) 2nd event: expected pattern (0:63) 3rd event: actual data read (0:63)

hpevtPltfrmStorageReadErr.name: hpevtPltfrmStorageReadErr
hpevtPltfrmStorageReadErr.description: System firmware was unable to complete a platform storage read command from the utilities system. The exact status printed in the data field.

hpevtPltfrmStorageWriteErr.name: hpevtPltfrmStorageWriteErr
hpevtPltfrmStorageWriteErr.description: System firmware was unable to complete a platform storage write command. The actual status is returned in the data field.

hpevtTreeNodeErrorSequencer.name: hpevtTreeNodeErrorSequencer
hpevtTreeNodeErrorSequencer.description: The Sequencer was unable to find the tree node it needed to complete an operation. The tree node is in the ASCII in the data field.

hpevtPartitionVariableError.name: hpevtPartitionVariableError
hpevtPartitionVariableError.description: System firmware attempted to read a partition variable from the GSP and store it in options. An error was encountered during this process. The data field contains the partition variable element ID that was being processed.

hpevtCellRedundtPowerFault.name: hpevtCellRedundtPowerFault
hpevtCellRedundtPowerFault.description: One or more power converters on the Cell or Cell Power Board has reported a fault. However, because of redundancy in the power system, the power to the Cell is still good. The data field contains detailed power fault location information that is specific to each platform.

hpevtPalProcConfigIncompatible.name: hpevtPalProcConfigIncompatible
hpevtPalProcConfigIncompatible.description: CPUProcConfigValue setting in options as been compared with what is reported by PAL as settable and CPUProcConfigValue is specifying at least one bit that is not supported by this version of PAL using the Get Processor Dependent Features. This chassis code is emitted in pairs, the first data field contains the PAL expected values; the second data field contains the requested setting from options.

hpevtPalGetProcFeaturesFailed.name: hpevtPalGetProcFeaturesFailed
hpevtPalGetProcFeaturesFailed.description: System firmware was unable to successfully issue the PAL_GET_PROC_FEATURES PAL proc. The data field is unused

hpevtPdhcCriticalDebug.name: hpevtPdhcCriticalDebug
hpevtPdhcCriticalDebug.description: This event is a tool to aid in the debugging and testing of firmware.

hpevtCluUndefinedCase.name: hpevtCluUndefinedCase
hpevtCluUndefinedCase.description: The CLU has encountered an undefined case in its control flow.

hpevtCellVoltageMarginUnkn.name: hpevtCellVoltageMarginUnkn
hpevtCellVoltageMarginUnkn.description: The Cell voltage margin settings do not match the Normal, +5%, or -5% values.

hpevtPdhcAssertionFailed.name: hpevtPdhcAssertionFailed
hpevtPdhcAssertionFailed.description: For debug purposes, many assumptions made by the PDHC developer(s) are checked at run-time. If this event log is seen, it indicates that the hardware or software is in an unknown state. For developer debug purposes, the data field describes where in the code that the error was detected. Data Bytes[0-1]: The line number within the source code file where the error was detected. Data Bytes[2-7]: The first 6 characters of the source code file name.

hpevtPdhcFirmwareUnknownErr.name: hpevtPdhcFirmwareUnknownErr
hpevtPdhcFirmwareUnknownErr.description: An unknown error has been detected by the PDHC firmware. For developer debug purposes, the data field describes where in the code that the error was detected. Data Bytes[0-1]: The line number within the source code file where the error was detected. Data Bytes[2-7]: The first 6 characters of the source code file name.

hpevtPdhcI2cWriteFailed.name: hpevtPdhcI2cWriteFailed
hpevtPdhcI2cWriteFailed.description: An attempt to write to a device on the PDHC's I2C bus has failed. The devices on the I2C bus are the Cell's FRU EEPROM, the Cell Power Board's FRU EEPROM, the voltage margining D-to-A converters, and, if they are accessible, the CPU Module Power Pods' FRU EEPROMs. The Data field information contains information that can identify the exact device that has failed. Refer to the Cell ERS for a mapping of I2C device addresses to devices. Data Bytes[0-1]: Reserved Data Bytes[2-3]: I2C Device Address Data Bytes[4-5]: Starting Word Address Data Bytes[6-7]: Size of attempted access (in bytes).

hpevtPdhcI2cReadFailed.name: hpevtPdhcI2cReadFailed
hpevtPdhcI2cReadFailed.description: An attempt to read from a device on the PDHC's I2C bus has failed. The devices on the I2C bus are the Cell's FRU EEPROM, the Cell Power Board's FRU EEPROM, the voltage margining D-to-A converters, and, if they are accessible, the CPU Module Power Pods' FRU EEPROMs. The Data field information contains information that can identify the exact device that has failed. Refer to the Cell ERS for a mapping of I2C device addresses to devices. Data Bytes[0-1]: Reserved Data Bytes[2-3]: I2C Device Address Data Bytes[4-5]: Starting Word Address Data Bytes[6-7]: Size of attempted access (in bytes).

hpevtPdhcSmbusWriteFailed.name: hpevtPdhcSmbusWriteFailed
hpevtPdhcSmbusWriteFailed.description: An attempt to write to a device on the PDHC's SM bus has failed. The devices on the SM bus are the CPU modules' FRU EEPROMs, the CPU modules' Processor Information ROMs, and the CPU modules' thermal sensors. The Data field information contains information that can identify the exact device that has failed. Refer to the Cell ERS for a mapping of SM Bus device addresses to devices. Data Bytes[0-1]: Reserved Data Bytes[2-3]: SM bus Device Address Data Bytes[4-5]: Starting Word Address Data Bytes[6-7]: Size of attempted access (in bytes).

hpevtPdhcSmbusReadFailed.name: hpevtPdhcSmbusReadFailed
hpevtPdhcSmbusReadFailed.description: An attempt to read from a device on the PDHC's SM bus has failed. The devices on the SM bus are the CPU modules' FRU EEPROMs, the CPU modules' Processor Information ROMs, and the CPU modules' thermal sensors. The Data field information contains information that can identify the exact device that has failed. Refer to the Cell ERS for a mapping of SM Bus device addresses to devices. Data Bytes[0-1]: Reserved Data Bytes[2-3]: SM bus Device Address Data Bytes[4-5]: Starting Word Address Data Bytes[6-7]: Size of attempted access (in bytes).

hpevtFrequencyProgramFailed.name: hpevtFrequencyProgramFailed
hpevtFrequencyProgramFailed.description: The PDHC did not read valid frequency information from the CPU modules' or Cell's FRU EEPROMs, or the frequency registers would not update properly. Following this event, the Cell will not boot until the problem is corrected and Cell Power has been turned off, then on again, using the PE command.

hpevtSysFwFlashUpdateError.name: hpevtSysFwFlashUpdateError
hpevtSysFwFlashUpdateError.description: An error has occurred while updating System FW. More details about the update failure may be available as displayed by the Firmware Update Utility (FWUU).

hpevtPdhcUnexpectedReset.name: hpevtPdhcUnexpectedReset
hpevtPdhcUnexpectedReset.description: The PDHC firmware was reset for some unknown reason.

hpevtCpuTmpSensorSetupFail.name: hpevtCpuTmpSensorSetupFail
hpevtCpuTmpSensorSetupFail.description: A hardware fault prevented the PDHC from configuring the thermal sensor(s) on one or more of the CPU modules. Following detection of this fault condition, the Cell will be prevented from booting until the Cell is powered 'off', then 'on', using the PE command.

hpevtCpuModuleThermalert.name: hpevtCpuModuleThermalert
hpevtCpuModuleThermalert.description: A CPU module's temperature has exceed the high temperature threshold. As a result of this event, an irrevocable 2 minute timer will begin. At the end of 2 minutes, the offending CPU module will be powered off by the Cell hardware. The Cell must be powered off then on using the MP's PE command before the CPU module will be powered again.

hpevtPdhcFlashUpdateError.name: hpevtPdhcFlashUpdateError
hpevtPdhcFlashUpdateError.description: An error occurred while updating the PDHC firmware. More specific details of the update error may be displayed by the Firmware Update utility running on the MP.

hpevtCellTypMismatchWSysfw.name: hpevtCellTypMismatchWSysfw
hpevtCellTypMismatchWSysfw.description: The cell type (IPF or PA) does not match System FW type. The cell type is detected based on information stored in CPU modules' FRUID EEPROMs. The System FW type is determined based on data that is embedded in the System FW ROM image. This is checked each time Cell power transitions from off to on, and each time the System FW is updated. Following the detection of this mismatch, the Cell will not be allowed to boot until the problem has been resolved.

hpevtPdhcPdhArbiterTimeout.name: hpevtPdhcPdhArbiterTimeout
hpevtPdhcPdhArbiterTimeout.description: This event is emitted after the PDHC has waited longer than a maximum expected time for the PDH arbiter to grant it control of the PDH bus. The PDHC will continue waiting for control of the PDH bus until the arbiter grants it control, or the Cell is powered off using the MP's PE command. While waiting for the PDH bus, the PDHC will NOT perform its normal duties such as monitoring the Cell status, and passing messages from the system to the MP, and the PDHC heartbeat will not blink.

hpevtPdhcGetSm4Timeout.name: hpevtPdhcGetSm4Timeout
hpevtPdhcGetSm4Timeout.description: This event is emitted after the PDHC has waited longer than a maximum expected time to obtain control of the PDH bus semaphore. The PDHC will continue waiting for control of the PDH bus semaphore until System FW relinquishes control of the semaphore, or the Cell is powered off using the MP's PE command. While waiting for the PDH bus semaphore, the PDHC will NOT perform its normal duties such as monitoring the Cell status, and passing messages from the system to the MP, and the PDHC heartbeat will not blink. The data field contains debug data that may be useful for developers. Data_byte[0] = last value read from PDHC's address for the microSemaphore register. Data_byte[1] = boolean indicator (1=set,0=not_set) of whether the PDHC's flag is set. Data_byte[2] = boolean indicator (1=set,0=not_set) of whether the System FW's flag is set.

hpevtIpmiBmc2hostMsgFailure.name: hpevtIpmiBmc2hostMsgFailure
hpevtIpmiBmc2hostMsgFailure.description: This event indicates that an error occurred while transmitting an IPMI message in the BMC2HOST direction. The data field contains more detailed information about the source of the error. Data Bytes 0 & 1 form a 16-bit IPMI error indicator that has the following values and meanings: 1 - IPMI_HOST_BUSY_TIMEOUT - The PDHC could not put a message in the BMC2HOST hardware message queue for over 10 seconds, so the pending message(s) were dropped. 2 - IPMI_INVALID_MSG_SIZE - The MP sent an IPMI message response that has an embedded size indicator that is less than 4 bytes or greater than the size of the message data. The poorly formed message response will be dropped. 3 - IPMI_BMC2HOST_Q_FULL - The BMC2HOST message queue in the PDHC is full, so a message response from the MP has been dropped.

hpevtEfiDebugLevelTokenErr.name: hpevtEfiDebugLevelTokenErr
hpevtEfiDebugLevelTokenErr.description: EFI was unable to read the initial debug level from the BMC token. EFI will continue with an unknown value for the debug level. Data Field: Return status from internal EFI function.

hpevtXbcPortNotLandmined.name: hpevtXbcPortNotLandmined
hpevtXbcPortNotLandmined.description: A XBC port was unexpectedly found to not be landmined. The data field consists of the XBC number (32:43) and the port number (44:55).

hpevtFabricValidateError.name: hpevtFabricValidateError
hpevtFabricValidateError.description: The number of landmined XBC ports was not within the allowable range. There is a minimum number of landmined ports because some ports are always unused. There is a maximum number of landmined ports because there is a limit to the number of broken links allowed in a system. The data field shows the number of landmined ports found

hpevtFabricISRInvalidBkp.name: hpevtFabricISRInvalidBkp
hpevtFabricISRInvalidBkp.description: Data field contains the backplane type found. During Intra SKD Routing, the backplane type detected was either a Medel backplane or was unrecognized. The backplane could therefore not be routed. This is a firmware sanity check. Data Field: system type

hpevtFabricXinWrZeroErrMaskError.name: hpevtFabricXinWrZeroErrMaskError
hpevtFabricXinWrZeroErrMaskError.description: Prior to initializing the CC to XBC link, the XIN error mask should be zeroed out to prevent spurious errors from interfering with the link initialization. This write to zero out the error mask failed. Data Field: (cell << 56) | return status

hpevtFabricCcPriModeRegRdStatus.name: hpevtFabricCcPriModeRegRdStatus
hpevtFabricCcPriModeRegRdStatus.description: The Coherency Controller's (CC) XIN link did not initialize properly. The data field contains the return status from an attempted read of the CC Primary Error Mode CSR. (0 = SUCCESS)

hpevtFabricCcPriModeRegRdData.name: hpevtFabricCcPriModeRegRdData
hpevtFabricCcPriModeRegRdData.description: The Coherency Controller's (CC) XIN link did not initialize properly. The data field contains the data read from the CC Primary Error Mode CSR.

hpevtFabricCcErrMaskRegRdStatus.name: hpevtFabricCcErrMaskRegRdStatus
hpevtFabricCcErrMaskRegRdStatus.description: The Coherency Controller's (CC) XIN link did not initialize properly. The data field contains the return status from an attempted read of the CC Primary Error Mode CSR. (0 = SUCCESS)

hpevtFabricCcErrMaskRegRdData.name: hpevtFabricCcErrMaskRegRdData
hpevtFabricCcErrMaskRegRdData.description: The Coherency Controller's (CC) XIN link did not initialize properly. The data field contains the data read from the CC Error Mask CSR.

hpevtFabricXingNeighborPortBad.name: hpevtFabricXingNeighborPortBad
hpevtFabricXingNeighborPortBad.description: The neighbor's port connected to the link being crossed is not routable. This was the first attempt to cross the link, PDC will now look for another link it can cross. DATA: (xbcNum << 32 ) | (port << 44)

hpevtFabricISRRdFwdProgErr.name: hpevtFabricISRRdFwdProgErr
hpevtFabricISRRdFwdProgErr.description: Fabric read error. Data field: (XBC number << 32 | return status)

hpevtFabricGetNeighborMaxLinksBroken.name: hpevtFabricGetNeighborMaxLinksBroken
hpevtFabricGetNeighborMaxLinksBroken.description: Too many crossbar links are broken. Cell cannot boot, halting. Data field: XBC number << 32

hpevtPmAssertionFailed.name: hpevtPmAssertionFailed
hpevtPmAssertionFailed.description: For debug purposes, many assumptions made by the PM developer(s) are checked at run-time. If this event log is seen, it will either indicate that the hardware is in a unknown state that is not handled by the PM, or that a programming bug has been found. For developer debug purposes, the data field describes where in the code that the error was detected. Data Bytes[0-1]: The line number within the source code file where the error was detected. Data Bytes[2-7]: The first 6 characters of the source code file name.

hpevtPmFirmwareUnknownErr.name: hpevtPmFirmwareUnknownErr
hpevtPmFirmwareUnknownErr.description: An unknown error has been detected by the PM firmware. For developer debug purposes, the data field describes where in the code that the error was detected. Data Bytes[0-1]: The line number within the source code file where the error was detected. Data Bytes[2-7]: The first 6 characters of the source code file name.

hpevtPmCriticalDebug.name: hpevtPmCriticalDebug
hpevtPmCriticalDebug.description: This event is a tool to aid in the debugging and testing of firmware.

hpevtFabricLinkCorErrTestFailure.name: hpevtFabricLinkCorErrTestFailure
hpevtFabricLinkCorErrTestFailure.description: Failed link testing to ensure that SBE and LPE errors are detected properly by the XBC. The XBC did not detect any errors. Data field indicates the return status: (1 = err detected, 0 = no err detected, -1 = XBC accesses failed)

hpevtInvalidCabinetNumber.name: hpevtInvalidCabinetNumber
hpevtInvalidCabinetNumber.description: The data field contains the cabinet number that is invalid

hpevtPdIncompatibleFwRevs.name: hpevtPdIncompatibleFwRevs
hpevtPdIncompatibleFwRevs.description: The cell indicated in the data field is at a different firmware revision than the reporting cell. This is determined by evaluating the checksums of the 2 rom images.

hpevtPmI2cWriteFailed.name: hpevtPmI2cWriteFailed
hpevtPmI2cWriteFailed.description: An attempt to write to a device on the PM's I2C bus has failed. The Data field contains information that can identify the exact device that has failed. Refer to the UGUY ERS for a mapping of I2C device addresses to devices. Data Bytes[0-1]: Reserved Data Bytes[2-3]: I2C Device Address Data Bytes[4-5]: Starting Word Address Data Bytes[6-7]: Size of attempted access (in bytes).

hpevtPmI2cReadFailed.name: hpevtPmI2cReadFailed
hpevtPmI2cReadFailed.description: An attempt to read from a device on the PM's I2C bus has failed. This event is only emitted when the PM is reading a BPS's. The Data field contains information that can identify the exact device that has failed. Refer to the UGUY ERS for a mapping of I2C device addresses to devices. Data Bytes[0-1]: Reserved Data Bytes[2-3]: I2C Device Address (to convert to BPS slot number subtract 1 and divide by 2) Data Bytes[4-5]: Starting Word Address Data Bytes[6-7]: Size of attempted access (in bytes).

hpevtCellInfoError.name: hpevtCellInfoError
hpevtCellInfoError.description: An error was encountered trying to obtain the data required for the cell information structure in ICM. The data field is an ASCII message that indicates the information that was not found.

hpevtSlaveConsoleSetupError.name: hpevtSlaveConsoleSetupError
hpevtSlaveConsoleSetupError.description: An error was encountered establishing the slave cells use of the diva console.

hpevtRegistryMoveToCoreCellError.name: hpevtRegistryMoveToCoreCellError
hpevtRegistryMoveToCoreCellError.description: An error was encountered trying to relocate the registry on a slave cell to point to the core cells main memory structures.

hpevtProfileGroupCCrcError.name: hpevtProfileGroupCCrcError
hpevtProfileGroupCCrcError.description: The Calculated CRC for the group C Partition Profile did not match the stored value. The expected value and the actual value will be emitted in 2 sequential chassis codes.

hpevtMcCoreCellSelectFail.name: hpevtMcCoreCellSelectFail
hpevtMcCoreCellSelectFail.description: Not able to find a core cell in the PD during a global MCA error processing.

hpevtFabricAssertFabricUtils.name: hpevtFabricAssertFabricUtils
hpevtFabricAssertFabricUtils.description: An unexpected error occurred while initializing the fabric. The firmware is not able to analyze this error. Clues to the cause of this error may be found in the IPMI forward progress log (FPL) either shortly before or after this log entry occurred. The FPL is available from the management processor using the 'sl' command. HP-UX also saves these logs in the /var/stm/logs/os directory, and they can be viewed using the slview utility.

hpevtSalPmiFwError.name: hpevtSalPmiFwError
hpevtSalPmiFwError.description: An internal firmware error was encountered. This is usually caused by a bad parameter passed to a function, corrupt memory, corrupt malloc tables or something similar. The data field contains the IP address of the function that encountered the error.

hpevtOlaWrongNumberCells.name: hpevtOlaWrongNumberCells
hpevtOlaWrongNumberCells.description: During the on line addition of a cell the partition adding the cell has determined inconsistent data as to which cell is being added. The cell addition will be aborted and the partition will resume execution without the new cell.

hpevtFabricXbcRouteSourceCellPortErr.name: hpevtFabricXbcRouteSourceCellPortErr
hpevtFabricXbcRouteSourceCellPortErr.description: An error occurred while reading the routing from the source cell's port on the source XBC. Data Field: (source cell << 56 | source XBC << 32)

hpevtBootOlaCellIncompatible.name: hpevtBootOlaCellIncompatible
hpevtBootOlaCellIncompatible.description: OLA cell cannot be added because it has resources that are not compatible with those already in the partition. Data field specifies the physical location of the cell which is incompatible and on which the OLA was attempted. The preceding chassis code or codes should already have been emitted specifying what the actual incompatibility was. The OLA cell will NOT be added to the partition, and the existing partition should not be affected.

hpevtBootOlaCellDidNotReachRendezvous.name: hpevtBootOlaCellDidNotReachRendezvous
hpevtBootOlaCellDidNotReachRendezvous.description: Root Cell attempted to OLA a cell which hung somewhere in the OLA process - the cell released from BIB but never made it to its final rendezvous state. Data field contains physical location of the hung OLA cell. The OLA cell will NOT be added to the partition, and the existing partition should not be affected.

hpevtBootOlaCellStillAtBib.name: hpevtBootOlaCellStillAtBib
hpevtBootOlaCellStillAtBib.description: Root cell attempted to OLA a cell that was never released from BIB. Data field contains the physical location of the cell that is being OLAD.

hpevtBootOlaCellUnexpectedCellState.name: hpevtBootOlaCellUnexpectedCellState
hpevtBootOlaCellUnexpectedCellState.description: Partition attempted to OLA a cell in an unexpected Cell state. Data Field contains the unexpected cell state of the OLA cell. The OLA cell will NOT be added to the partition, and the existing partition should not be affected.

hpevtBootOlaCellCantReachAliveCells.name: hpevtBootOlaCellCantReachAliveCells
hpevtBootOlaCellCantReachAliveCells.description: Root cell will emit this chassis code indicating the OLA cell could reach all cells in the alive set of the existing partition. Data field will contain the physical location of the OLA cell. This chassis code should immediately follow a chassis code indicating exactly which cell the OLA cell could not reach. The OLA cell will not be added to the partition and the partition will be unaffected.

hpevtBootMixedCpuCoreFreqInstalled.name: hpevtBootMixedCpuCoreFreqInstalled
hpevtBootMixedCpuCoreFreqInstalled.description: CPU's of mixed maximum core frequencies are installed

hpevtXinInitIntermittentFailure.name: hpevtXinInitIntermittentFailure
hpevtXinInitIntermittentFailure.description: The Cell Controller-XBC link initialization is having an intermittent failure. The data field contains the number of initialization sequences that failed before being successful.

hpevtPdhErrClearOlaSteeringBit.name: hpevtPdhErrClearOlaSteeringBit
hpevtPdhErrClearOlaSteeringBit.description: PDC failed clearing the OLA steering bit in the PDH FPGA microstatus register. Data field contains the physical location of the cell with the failure. This can only happen on an OLA cell and will cause that cell to reset and not to join the existing partition.

hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdatePdAddrMap.name: hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdatePdAddrMap
hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdatePdAddrMap.description: The attempt to update the PD Addr Map to include OLA cell failed.

hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdatePdPdt.name: hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdatePdPdt
hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdatePdPdt.description: Attempt to update the partition PDT with OLA cell PDT data has failed.

hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdateCellMap.name: hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdateCellMap
hpevtBootOlaFailedUpdateCellMap.description: Attempt to update the cell map to include the OLA Cell failed

hpevtFabricCc2XbcLinkInitFailed.name: hpevtFabricCc2XbcLinkInitFailed
hpevtFabricCc2XbcLinkInitFailed.description: Fabric Discovery's final attempt to initialize the local cell's CC to Crossbar Chip (XBC) link has failed. This cell cannot talk to the fabric. Data: link init state bit read from the CC Link State register

hpevtFwVirtualMappingError.name: hpevtFwVirtualMappingError
hpevtFwVirtualMappingError.description: An internal firmware error was encountered. This is usually caused by a bad parameter passed to a function, corrupt memory, corrupt malloc tables or something similar. The data field contains the physical address that failed mapping to a virtual address

hpevtFabricXinInitWriteErr.name: hpevtFabricXinInitWriteErr
hpevtFabricXinInitWriteErr.description: Failure while writing the XBC CSR containing the link status

hpevtFabricXinInitReadErr.name: hpevtFabricXinInitReadErr
hpevtFabricXinInitReadErr.description: Failure while reading the XBC CSR containing the link status

hpevtFabricLinkInitIntermittentFailure.name: hpevtFabricLinkInitIntermittentFailure
hpevtFabricLinkInitIntermittentFailure.description: Fabric Discovery's attempt to initialize the local cell's CC to XBC link has failed. The link initialization sequence has an intermittent problem.

hpevtIodiscPciInitnodeError.name: hpevtIodiscPciInitnodeError
hpevtIodiscPciInitnodeError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to create and initialize a PCI device node

hpevtIodiscPciBusscanError.name: hpevtIodiscPciBusscanError
hpevtIodiscPciBusscanError.description: An error was encountered while scanning the PCI bus

hpevtIodiscPciInitbridgeError.name: hpevtIodiscPciInitbridgeError
hpevtIodiscPciInitbridgeError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to initialize a P2P bridge

hpevtIodiscPciIomapError.name: hpevtIodiscPciIomapError
hpevtIodiscPciIomapError.description: Insufficient IO Port space to support the PCI card

hpevtIodiscPciMmiomapError.name: hpevtIodiscPciMmiomapError
hpevtIodiscPciMmiomapError.description: Insufficient MMIO space to support the PCI card requirements

hpevtIodiscSbaInitnodeError.name: hpevtIodiscSbaInitnodeError
hpevtIodiscSbaInitnodeError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to initialize the SBA node

hpevtIodiscSbaDiscoverError.name: hpevtIodiscSbaDiscoverError
hpevtIodiscSbaDiscoverError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to discover SBA hardware

hpevtIodiscSbaResetError.name: hpevtIodiscSbaResetError
hpevtIodiscSbaResetError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to reset the SBA

hpevtIodiscIolinkError.name: hpevtIodiscIolinkError
hpevtIodiscIolinkError.description: An error was detected in the link between the CC and the I/O controller.

hpevtIodiscCableError.name: hpevtIodiscCableError
hpevtIodiscCableError.description: An SBA cable error has been detected

hpevtIodiscIoChassisPower.name: hpevtIodiscIoChassisPower
hpevtIodiscIoChassisPower.description: Identified the cell number that is connected to the chassis.

hpevtIodiscLbaInitnodeError.name: hpevtIodiscLbaInitnodeError
hpevtIodiscLbaInitnodeError.description: An error occurred while attempting to create or initialize an LBA node

hpevtIodiscLbaWidthError.name: hpevtIodiscLbaWidthError
hpevtIodiscLbaWidthError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to configure LBA rope bundling width

hpevtIodiscLbaClearError.name: hpevtIodiscLbaClearError
hpevtIodiscLbaClearError.description: An error occurred while attempting to clear an LBA error log register

hpevtIodiscLbaLogError.name: hpevtIodiscLbaLogError
hpevtIodiscLbaLogError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to generate LBA error logs

hpevtIodiscLbaDiscoverError.name: hpevtIodiscLbaDiscoverError
hpevtIodiscLbaDiscoverError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to discover LBA hardware

hpevtIodiscLbaConfigError.name: hpevtIodiscLbaConfigError
hpevtIodiscLbaConfigError.description: An error occurred while attempting to configure the LBA hardware

hpevtIodiscLbaPciscanError.name: hpevtIodiscLbaPciscanError
hpevtIodiscLbaPciscanError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to scan the PCI bus

hpevtIodiscLbaPciconfigError.name: hpevtIodiscLbaPciconfigError
hpevtIodiscLbaPciconfigError.description: An error was encountered while attempting to configure PCI config space

hpevtBootOlaCellErrAccessCmplxProfile.name: hpevtBootOlaCellErrAccessCmplxProfile
hpevtBootOlaCellErrAccessCmplxProfile.description: The OLA cell failed accessing the complex profile. Cell will send Failed to OLA message back to partition and then reboot itself. Existing partition will not be affected.

hpevtBootFwRelocMemErr.name: hpevtBootFwRelocMemErr
hpevtBootFwRelocMemErr.description: A Firmware tries to find a main memory block large enough meeting alignment requirements.

hpevtBootOlaCellNotConfigInCmplxProfile.name: hpevtBootOlaCellNotConfigInCmplxProfile
hpevtBootOlaCellNotConfigInCmplxProfile.description: Cell started OLA but is not configured in the complex profile of the partition. Cell will reboot to SINC_BIB. Existing partition will not be affected.

hpevtOptsNvmAllocError.name: hpevtOptsNvmAllocError
hpevtOptsNvmAllocError.description: The Options service received an error when attempting to allocate an NVRAM storage block. Either an error was returned from the call, or the call returned successfully yet an invalid address was returned.

hpevtBootOlaUpdateRtcFailedOlaCell.name: hpevtBootOlaUpdateRtcFailedOlaCell
hpevtBootOlaUpdateRtcFailedOlaCell.description: A failure occurred on the OLA cell during the attempt to synchronize its real time clock with the clock(s) in the existing partition. Data field contains physical location of OLA cell.

hpevtSalInfoTimeout.name: hpevtSalInfoTimeout
hpevtSalInfoTimeout.description: Access to SAL error log procedure timed out because the log facility was busy processing a request from another CPU. Data field indicates the SAL procedure ID.

hpevtPdhIprNotClearedOnCell.name: hpevtPdhIprNotClearedOnCell
hpevtPdhIprNotClearedOnCell.description: The PDH FPGA IPR is not cleared after a MAX_RD_CLR_IPR_TRIES on a cell. The Data Filed in the Cell number. See the next Chassis Code to see the MAX_RD_CLR_IPR_TRIES

hpevtPdhIprClearAttempts.name: hpevtPdhIprClearAttempts
hpevtPdhIprClearAttempts.description: Indicated the PDH FPGA IPR is not cleared after a number of PDC attempts. The Data Field contents the MAX_RD_CLR_IPR_TRIES. Please look at the previous Chassis Code to see the Cell number.

hpevtBootOlaUpdateRtcFailedExistingCell.name: hpevtBootOlaUpdateRtcFailedExistingCell
hpevtBootOlaUpdateRtcFailedExistingCell.description: attempt to synchronize the Real-Time Clock of the OLA cell with the existing partition failed because the RTC on the core cell could not be read.

hpevtMemIncompleteEchelon.name: hpevtMemIncompleteEchelon
hpevtMemIncompleteEchelon.description: One or more dimms are missing from the echelon given in the data field. The dimms may not be installed or firmware was not able to detect the dimms.

hpevtFabricRdPortStatePortInvalid.name: hpevtFabricRdPortStatePortInvalid
hpevtFabricRdPortStatePortInvalid.description: The code that reads the port state (landmine vs. healthy) expects a XBC internal port number, it received bogus data. The port state cannot be read. Data Field: (port << 44) | (xbc num << 32)

hpevtFabricWrPortStatePortInvalid.name: hpevtFabricWrPortStatePortInvalid
hpevtFabricWrPortStatePortInvalid.description: The code that writes the port state (landmine vs. healthy) expects a XBC internal port number, it received bogus data. The port state cannot be read. Data Field: (port << 44) | (xbc num << 32)

hpevtMainBpLpmFlt.name: hpevtMainBpLpmFlt
hpevtMainBpLpmFlt.description: The main backplane is reporting the LPM status as fault.

hpevtIoBpLpmFlt.name: hpevtIoBpLpmFlt
hpevtIoBpLpmFlt.description: The IO backplane has reported a local power monitor fault.

hpevtCmplxProfileInitFailed.name: hpevtCmplxProfileInitFailed
hpevtCmplxProfileInitFailed.description: System firmware was unable to default the complex profile

hpevtPalSetProcFeaturesFailed.name: hpevtPalSetProcFeaturesFailed
hpevtPalSetProcFeaturesFailed.description: Firmware call to set processor feature resulted in an error.

hpevtActiveLogNotFound.name: hpevtActiveLogNotFound
hpevtActiveLogNotFound.description: This chassis code shows that the error log space in the NVRAM has not been allocated for the current error event. This will be emitted out whenever a error section is attempted to be logged without allocation of log space in NVRAM

hpevtReachedMaxErrorLogs.name: hpevtReachedMaxErrorLogs
hpevtReachedMaxErrorLogs.description: This indicates that the error logs for a particular event type have reached the maximum allowed to be stored in the NVRAM. The event type is indicated in the data field.

hpevtOldNoCellToDelete.name: hpevtOldNoCellToDelete
hpevtOldNoCellToDelete.description: System firmware has been invoked to perform a cell delete operation but no cell in the system appears to be ready for deletion.

hpevtBpsOvercurrent.name: hpevtBpsOvercurrent
hpevtBpsOvercurrent.description: The bulk power supply is overcurrent

hpevtErmOutOfHeap.name: hpevtErmOutOfHeap
hpevtErmOutOfHeap.description: Error Response Mode code attempted a malloc of heap space that failed.

hpevtMemDimmUnsupported.name: hpevtMemDimmUnsupported
hpevtMemDimmUnsupported.description: The dimm in the physical location given by the data field is not supported on this platform. The dimm may not be supported by the hardware, or the dimm may not have been properly qualified for this platform.

hpevtOptsMallocError.name: hpevtOptsMallocError
hpevtOptsMallocError.description: The OPTIONS component was unable to allocate NVRAM memory in order to store a non-volatile variable. The storage area for NVRAM options may be full, or there may be undetected corruption.

hpevtCellHwDegraded.name: hpevtCellHwDegraded
hpevtCellHwDegraded.description: A dimm or CPU has failed and is not operational for the system. This event is emitted prior to determining if the cell should be integrated into the Partition.

hpevtNotIntegratingCell.name: hpevtNotIntegratingCell
hpevtNotIntegratingCell.description: A cpu or dimm error has been detected, and the Complex Profile, Cell Integration Table, Cell integration policy says to not integrate the cell into the PD. The data field is unused, but the cell that emitted this event is the one that did not get integrated.

hpevtIoContextCorruptErr.name: hpevtIoContextCorruptErr
hpevtIoContextCorruptErr.description: The IO error context is corrupt. This will impair IO error reporting.

hpevtIoRopeFatal.name: hpevtIoRopeFatal
hpevtIoRopeFatal.description: A rope went fatal from the SBA to the LBA. If all the ropes go fatal the IO subsystem is dead. Any I/O below the rope will not be accessible. The data field gives the physical location of the rope that went fatal. Some ROPE_FATAL conditions will not cause the system to go down. For Example, a rope that has gone fatal during an OLAR operation will only cause warnings to the user, not bring the partition down.

hpevtIoBusFatal.name: hpevtIoBusFatal
hpevtIoBusFatal.description: A PCI bus on the system is fatal. Any device on this bus is unavailable. Firmware was unable to complete card initialization due to an error. Data field contains physical location of failed bus.

hpevtIoRopeUnitFatal.name: hpevtIoRopeUnitFatal
hpevtIoRopeUnitFatal.description: One of the rope units in the SBA failed. If all of the rope units fail, then IO will not be available on this cell.

hpevtPdhFlashWriteEnableBitSetNowCleared.name: hpevtPdhFlashWriteEnableBitSetNowCleared
hpevtPdhFlashWriteEnableBitSetNowCleared.description: The System Flash Write Enable bit is incorrectly set and now clearing by PDC. The Data field contains the value of PDH Miscellaneous Signal Register read before System Flash bit is cleared.

hpevtFirmwareInitError.name: hpevtFirmwareInitError
hpevtFirmwareInitError.description: System firmware encountered an error while trying to perform an operation during system initialization. This event ID will always be emitted before an event ID that describes the status of the operation that failed.

hpevtMcIncompleteCpuSet.name: hpevtMcIncompleteCpuSet
hpevtMcIncompleteCpuSet.description: This means that all the cpus in the cell did not show up.

hpevtMcIncompleteCellSet.name: hpevtMcIncompleteCellSet
hpevtMcIncompleteCellSet.description: This means that all the cells did not rendezvous during the PD rendezvous. The data part will contain the Expected data and the actual mask of the cells that rendezvoused.

hpevtMcTreeCheckFailed.name: hpevtMcTreeCheckFailed
hpevtMcTreeCheckFailed.description: The FW tree sanity check failed during the MCA error processing.

hpevtMcRegistryCheckFailed.name: hpevtMcRegistryCheckFailed
hpevtMcRegistryCheckFailed.description: This means that the registry sanity check failed during MCA error handling.

hpevtMcDuringOsMca.name: hpevtMcDuringOsMca
hpevtMcDuringOsMca.description: This means that MCA occurred while OS_MCA was performing error recovery.

hpevtMcMemDumpAbandon.name: hpevtMcMemDumpAbandon
hpevtMcMemDumpAbandon.description: This means that memory dump will be abandoned due to work-around for CN2272. This happens when one of the Blocking timeout in the Processor input block of the Cell Controller occurs.

hpevtMcFwTreeNotComplete.name: hpevtMcFwTreeNotComplete
hpevtMcFwTreeNotComplete.description: The firmware tree is not complete and hence there will be no PD rendezvous.

hpevtAcpiConfigMismatch.name: hpevtAcpiConfigMismatch
hpevtAcpiConfigMismatch.description: The firmware parameter that defines the ACPI configuration is inconsistent in at least one of the cells in the partition.

hpevtFabricXinErrOrderStatusClrFailed.name: hpevtFabricXinErrOrderStatusClrFailed
hpevtFabricXinErrOrderStatusClrFailed.description: Writing the XIN_ERR_ORDER_STATUS register of the CC failed. This is some sort of a hardware failure. Data Field: return status

hpevtFabricAssertFabricInit.name: hpevtFabricAssertFabricInit
hpevtFabricAssertFabricInit.description: An unexpected error occurred while initializing the fabric. The firmware is not able to analyze this error. Clues to the cause of this error may be found in the IPMI forward progress log (FPL) either shortly before or after this log entry occurred. The FPL is available from the management processor using the 'sl' command. HP-UX also saves these logs in the /var/stm/logs/os directory, and they can be viewed using the slview utility.

hpevtInvalidPiromData.name: hpevtInvalidPiromData
hpevtInvalidPiromData.description: A value read by the PDHC from a CPU module's Processor Information ROM was not within acceptable limits.

hpevtSettingFreqRatiosError.name: hpevtSettingFreqRatiosError
hpevtSettingFreqRatiosError.description: An invalid parameter was specified when trying to set the cpu bus config register, cpu frequencies ratio field. Valid range is 0xe - 0x17

hpevtOptsBlockCksumError.name: hpevtOptsBlockCksumError
hpevtOptsBlockCksumError.description: The overhead structure of the OPTIONS block in NVRAM has a checksum error.

hpevtFabricColaLocalCcLinkNotInit.name: hpevtFabricColaLocalCcLinkNotInit
hpevtFabricColaLocalCcLinkNotInit.description: During a cell OLA, the link on the local cell failed to initialize. Data Field: (my cell << 32) | XIN Link State

hpevtFabricXinInitDisableWrError.name: hpevtFabricXinInitDisableWrError
hpevtFabricXinInitDisableWrError.description: An attempt to disable the fabric link failed because writing the CC CSR failed. Data Field: (cell << 56) | return status

hpevtFabricXinErrMaskUnknownBkp.name: hpevtFabricXinErrMaskUnknownBkp
hpevtFabricXinErrMaskUnknownBkp.description: Could not determine the system type in order to write the appropriate error mask for the fabric link. Data Field: system type

hpevtFabricXinWrErrMaskError.name: hpevtFabricXinWrErrMaskError
hpevtFabricXinWrErrMaskError.description: Failed writing the XIN error mask for CC's fabric link. Data Field: (cell << 56) | return status

hpevtFabricXinRdErrMaskError.name: hpevtFabricXinRdErrMaskError
hpevtFabricXinRdErrMaskError.description: Could not read the XIN Link error mask register. Data Field: (cell << 56) | return status

hpevtFabricInitCcLinkFailure.name: hpevtFabricInitCcLinkFailure
hpevtFabricInitCcLinkFailure.description: The CC to CC link initialization sequence has failed. Data Field: link init status

hpevtResetCommandError.name: hpevtResetCommandError
hpevtResetCommandError.description: An error occurred while trying to notify the MP that a reset is about to occur (QPartitionReleaseBIB command). The status is in the data field.

hpevtFabricInitCcLinkDisableErr.name: hpevtFabricInitCcLinkDisableErr
hpevtFabricInitCcLinkDisableErr.description: A fabric access error occurred while trying to disable the CC to CC link on a single cell Medel system. This cell will halt. Data field: error status

hpevtFabricSetPortStateGetSm4Err.name: hpevtFabricSetPortStateGetSm4Err
hpevtFabricSetPortStateGetSm4Err.description: While updating the Port State register, the cell could not get the XBC semaphore. Data field is: (Port Num << 44 | XBC num << 32 | return status). Where return status is: (0 Success; -1 Access Failure; -2 Semaphore Owned By Another, -3 Semaphore Already Owned; -4 XBC Key Contention)

hpevtFabricSetPortStateRlsSm4Err.name: hpevtFabricSetPortStateRlsSm4Err
hpevtFabricSetPortStateRlsSm4Err.description: While updating the Port State register, the cell could not get the XBC semaphore. Data field is: (Port Num << 44 | XBC num << 32 | return status). Where return status is: (0 Success; -1 Generic Failure)

hpevtFabricAssertFabricErr.name: hpevtFabricAssertFabricErr
hpevtFabricAssertFabricErr.description: An unexpected error occurred while initializing the fabric. The firmware is not able to analyze this error. Clues to the cause of this error may be found in the IPMI forward progress log (FPL) either shortly before or after this log entry occurred. The FPL is available from the management processor using the 'sl' command. HP-UX also saves these logs in the /var/stm/logs/os directory, and they can be viewed using the slview utility.

hpevtFabricXinLinkAlreadyInit.name: hpevtFabricXinLinkAlreadyInit
hpevtFabricXinLinkAlreadyInit.description: While attempting to initialize the XIN link, it was found to already be initialized. A firmware assertion has failed. The link will not be re-initialized and processing should continue as normal. However, the system could be confused at this point.

hpevtNoCpuModulesFoundByPdhc.name: hpevtNoCpuModulesFoundByPdhc
hpevtNoCpuModulesFoundByPdhc.description: The PDHC FW could not detect any CPU modules on its Cell board, so it is holding the Cell in reset.

hpevtCpuModCompatMismatch.name: hpevtCpuModCompatMismatch
hpevtCpuModCompatMismatch.description: The Cell has been disabled by PDHC FW because the CPU modules are not compatible. Compatibility is determined based on data stored in the Scratch/FRUID EEPROM on each CPU module. The CPU module partition compatibility byte for each CPU module must be identical.

hpevtBadCpuModScratchCksum.name: hpevtBadCpuModScratchCksum
hpevtBadCpuModScratchCksum.description: The Cell has been disabled because of invalid data in a CPU module Scratch EEPROM. PDHC FW checksums the FRUID data stored in each CPU module's Scratch EEPROM. If a checksum fails, the Cell is held in reset and will not boot. The data field identifies the CPU module that failed.

hpevtPdhBatteryLowWarning.name: hpevtPdhBatteryLowWarning
hpevtPdhBatteryLowWarning.description: The battery voltage level is low for the cell. This indicates that the NVRAM will not be saved if the power is removed.

hpevtFabricRouteXbcCopyRoutingErr.name: hpevtFabricRouteXbcCopyRoutingErr
hpevtFabricRouteXbcCopyRoutingErr.description: There was an error while copying the routing for the XBC to the local XBC port. The cell will reset. Data: (XBC port << 44) | (XBC num << 32) | return status

hpevtFabricCopyRdBackFailed.name: hpevtFabricCopyRdBackFailed
hpevtFabricCopyRdBackFailed.description: The read immediately after a write while copying routing registers failed. Data: whether or not the XBC Key was enabled

hpevtFabricRtgCompleteSm4RlsErr.name: hpevtFabricRtgCompleteSm4RlsErr
hpevtFabricRtgCompleteSm4RlsErr.description: Failed to release a XBC Semaphore while marking each XBC in the complex to indicate that routing has completed. Data: (XBC num << 32) | return value

hpevtFabricRtgCompleteWrFwdPrgErr.name: hpevtFabricRtgCompleteWrFwdPrgErr
hpevtFabricRtgCompleteWrFwdPrgErr.description: Writing this XBC's forward progress register failed. Data: (XBC num << 32) | return value

hpevtFabricRtgCompleteSm4AccessErr.name: hpevtFabricRtgCompleteSm4AccessErr
hpevtFabricRtgCompleteSm4AccessErr.description: Failed to get a XBC Semaphore while marking each XBC in the complex to indicate that routing has completed. Skipping this XBC. Data: (XBC num << 32) | return value

hpevtFabricRtgCompleteTopologyErr.name: hpevtFabricRtgCompleteTopologyErr
hpevtFabricRtgCompleteTopologyErr.description: Reading this XBC's topology register failed. Data Field: (xbc num << 32) | return status

hpevtFabricRouteTraversableCc2CcErr.name: hpevtFabricRouteTraversableCc2CcErr
hpevtFabricRouteTraversableCc2CcErr.description: Could not check the traversability between two cells on an XBCless platform. Data field: return status (1 = SUCCESS, 0 = FALSE, -1 = FAILURE)

hpevtFabricDataRouteTraversableCc2CcErr.name: hpevtFabricDataRouteTraversableCc2CcErr
hpevtFabricDataRouteTraversableCc2CcErr.description: Could not check the traversability between two cells on an XBCless platform. Data field: return status (1 = SUCCESS, 0 = FALSE, -1 = FAILURE)

hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseLclXinRdErr.name: hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseLclXinRdErr
hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseLclXinRdErr.description: While checking traversability of a 2 cell back to back system, there was an error reading the local cell's XIN block. Data Field: return status (1 or -1)

hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseRmtXinRdErr.name: hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseRmtXinRdErr
hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseRmtXinRdErr.description: While checking traversability of a 2 cell back to back system, there was an error reading the local cell's XIN block. Data Field: return status (1 or -1)

hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseLclNotInit.name: hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseLclNotInit
hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseLclNotInit.description: Could not traverse to the target cell. The XIN link is either not initialized, or is not connected to the target cell. However, the target cell is designated to be within the partition. Data Field: target cell << 56 | XIN link state register

hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseRmtNotInit.name: hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseRmtNotInit
hpevtFabricCc2ccTraverseRmtNotInit.description: Could not traverse to the target cell. The XIN link is either not initialized, or is not connected to the target cell. However, the target cell is designated to be within the partition. Data Field: target cell << 56 | XIN link state register

hpevtFabricDisableXinLinkReadErr.name: hpevtFabricDisableXinLinkReadErr
hpevtFabricDisableXinLinkReadErr.description: Error reading the XIN_LINK_STATE register of the CC. This occurred while verifying that the link had been disabled. Data Field: cell being read << 56 | return status from the CSR read.

hpevtFabricXinInitRetryReadErr.name: hpevtFabricXinInitRetryReadErr
hpevtFabricXinInitRetryReadErr.description: Failure while reading the XBC CSR containing the link status. This occurred while attempting the retry process to get XBC to CC link initialized. Data Field: link init status

hpevtFabricAssertFabricCc.name: hpevtFabricAssertFabricCc
hpevtFabricAssertFabricCc.description: An unexpected error occurred while initializing the fabric. The firmware is not able to analyze this error. Clues to the cause of this error may be found in the IPMI forward progress log (FPL) either shortly before or after this log entry occurred. The FPL is available from the management processor using the 'sl' command. HP-UX also saves these logs in the /var/stm/logs/os directory, and they can be viewed using the slview utility.
