hpevtCpuRestricted.name: hpevtCpuRestricted
hpevtCpuRestricted.description: The CPU that just completed self tests is functionally or performance restricted. The data field contains the Self Test State Parameter. The 2-bit state field (bits 1..0) can have the following values when this event is displayed: 01 - Performance Restricted - cpu still functions 10 - Functionally Restricted - cpu doesn't function properly

hpevtPdhInvalidRtcCleared.name: hpevtPdhInvalidRtcCleared
hpevtPdhInvalidRtcCleared.description: The RTC was found to be invalid and has been cleared

hpevtLstNotRun.name: hpevtLstNotRun
hpevtLstNotRun.description: System firmware requested that Late Self Tests be run by PAL, but PAL returned that the tests did not actually run on the processor. The data field indicates the status word returned by PAL.

hpevtBootSetCellStateFabricFailure.name: hpevtBootSetCellStateFabricFailure
hpevtBootSetCellStateFabricFailure.description: An attempt to update the cell state has failed due to a fabric crossbar failure. The cell number being updated in bits 63:56, while the traversable cell set (those cells connected to the fabric) is returned in bits 31:0

hpevtBootResetCellStateFailure.name: hpevtBootResetCellStateFailure
hpevtBootResetCellStateFailure.description: Failed to reset a cell due to an error setting the cell's state. The cell will not be reset with the other cells in the PD. The cell number is reported in the data field.

hpevtMemChipspareDeallocRank.name: hpevtMemChipspareDeallocRank
hpevtMemChipspareDeallocRank.description: SFW has detected that a DRAM is failing on the DIMM specified by the physical location. The rank the failing DIMM is part of will be deallocated.

hpevtClockFreqError.name: hpevtClockFreqError
hpevtClockFreqError.description: Internal CPU clocks are not valid when compared with the real time clock. The data field contains the hex value of the elapsed time. If this value is off a small percentage from the expected value (which is given in the next chassis code), the event is emitted.

hpevtFabricColaInitTraversableErr.name: hpevtFabricColaInitTraversableErr
hpevtFabricColaInitTraversableErr.description: Could not traverse the fabric to the cell being added. Data field: (chosen cell << 56) | return status, where -1 = failure

hpevtFabricAttemptFocusedReroute.name: hpevtFabricAttemptFocusedReroute
hpevtFabricAttemptFocusedReroute.description: A XBC port was found to be unhealthy on this reboot. This cell will attempt to route around it. Data field: (local Cell << 56) | (local internal Port << 44) | (local XBC << 32) | XBC internal port number being routed around.

hpevtFabricCellRerouteNinfoErr.name: hpevtFabricCellRerouteNinfoErr
hpevtFabricCellRerouteNinfoErr.description: Error getting the XBC port's expected neighbor from a firmware table. Data field: 0 (SUCCESS) or -1 (FAILURE)

hpevtBootWakeCpuIsCpuDeconfigErr.name: hpevtBootWakeCpuIsCpuDeconfigErr
hpevtBootWakeCpuIsCpuDeconfigErr.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition. The data field contains the error return value from PDC function IsHCellCpuDeconfig().

hpevtBootWakeCpuGetCountersErr.name: hpevtBootWakeCpuGetCountersErr
hpevtBootWakeCpuGetCountersErr.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition. The data field contains the error return value from PDC function SleepAndWakeupCountersGet().

hpevtBootWakeCpuGetStructAddrErr.name: hpevtBootWakeCpuGetStructAddrErr
hpevtBootWakeCpuGetStructAddrErr.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition. The data field contains the error return value from PDC function PdhGetHCellStructAddr().

hpevtBootCheckCpu4CompletionErr.name: hpevtBootCheckCpu4CompletionErr
hpevtBootCheckCpu4CompletionErr.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition. The data field contains the error return value from PDC function HasCpuCompletedWakeupTask().

hpevtBootCheckCpuGetStructAddrErr.name: hpevtBootCheckCpuGetStructAddrErr
hpevtBootCheckCpuGetStructAddrErr.description: Either PDC is going to halt the cell or reset the partition because PDC was unable to access the PDH memory of either its local cell or another cell in the partition. The data field contains the error return value from PDC function PdhGetHCellStructAddr().

hpevtReconfigResetScheduled.name: hpevtReconfigResetScheduled
hpevtReconfigResetScheduled.description: There is a need to reset the cell for reconfiguration, but it cannot be done yet because the cell has not reported at BIB. The Reset is being scheduled to be performed later.

hpevtProfileWrongArchType.name: hpevtProfileWrongArchType
hpevtProfileWrongArchType.description: When processing the complex profile, the an unexpected 'Architecture Type' was specified in the PA/IA Arch field. The actual data found is displayed.

hpevtBootCheckCpuIsDeconfigErr.name: hpevtBootCheckCpuIsDeconfigErr
hpevtBootCheckCpuIsDeconfigErr.description: While trying to determine whether or not a particular processor has completed the task for which it was awakened, PDC was unable to access the deconfig byte information about the target processor. A processor should always be able to access this data in PDH memory for any processor on its own cell and for any processor on a cell that is alive in the partition. Therefore, PDC is either going to halt the cell or reset the partition because of this problem. The data field contains the PDC error return status from IsHCellCpuDeconfig().

hpevtBootCheckCpuGetCountersErr.name: hpevtBootCheckCpuGetCountersErr
hpevtBootCheckCpuGetCountersErr.description: While trying to determine whether or not a particular processor has completed the task for which it was awakened, PDC was unable to access the CPU's sleep and wakeup counters for the target processor. A processor should always be able to access this data in PDH memory for any processor on its own cell and for any processor on a cell that is alive in the partition. Therefore, PDC is either going to halt the cell or reset the partition because of this problem. The data field contains the PDC error return status from SleepAndWakeupCountersGet().

hpevtBootPdMonarchRtnFromSwSetFpErr.name: hpevtBootPdMonarchRtnFromSwSetFpErr
hpevtBootPdMonarchRtnFromSwSetFpErr.description: While trying to determine whether or not a particular processor has completed the task for which it was awakened, PDC was unable to access the CPU's forward progress state (i.e. PST state) for the target processor. A processor should always be able to access this data in PDH memory for any processor on its own cell and for any processor on a cell that is alive in the partition. Therefore, PDC is either going to halt the cell or reset the partition because of this problem. The data field contains the PDC error return status from CpuFpSet().

hpevtBootSlaveRtnFromFwSetFpErr.name: hpevtBootSlaveRtnFromFwSetFpErr
hpevtBootSlaveRtnFromFwSetFpErr.description: While trying to determine whether or not a particular processor has completed the task for which it was awakened, PDC was unable to access the CPU's Forward Progress State (i.e. PST state) for the target processor. A processor should always be able to access this data in PDH memory for any processor on its own cell and for any processor on a cell that is alive in the partition. Therefore, PDC is either going to halt the cell or reset the partition because of this problem. The data field contains the PDC error return status from CpuFpSet().

hpevtBootProblemBranchingToPgzLocation.name: hpevtBootProblemBranchingToPgzLocation
hpevtBootProblemBranchingToPgzLocation.description: At a certain point in PDC boot, all of the processors in the partition except the PD monarch are put into a sleep, and they remain there until they are awakened by the PD monarch, at which time they read an architected location in Page Zero to find out where to branch to. This gives the OS a mechanism by which to bring processors under its control and have it executing OS code. This chassis log is sent if and when a problem is detected by PDC regarding the contents in the Page Zero location. This means that PDC cannot branch to the location logged in the Page Zero location. So, PDC sends this chassis log and then the processor returns to sleep. The data field is unused.

hpevtBootBadCpuOrder.name: hpevtBootBadCpuOrder
hpevtBootBadCpuOrder.description: The Data Field contains the value used to determine a valid order.

hpevtBootSlpWakeCntrsStructAddrErr.name: hpevtBootSlpWakeCntrsStructAddrErr
hpevtBootSlpWakeCntrsStructAddrErr.description: While trying to get the sleep counter and the wakeup counter for a particular processor, which is kept in a data structure in PDH memory, PDC was unable to determine the address to the data structure on the remote cell. PDC is supposed to be able to calculate addresses to anything in PDH memory on other cells in the partition. The data field contains the PDC error return status from a function called PdhGetHCellStructAddr().

hpevtBootGetSleepTimeoutStructAddrErr.name: hpevtBootGetSleepTimeoutStructAddrErr
hpevtBootGetSleepTimeoutStructAddrErr.description: Error occurred accessing a PDC data structure. Depending upon the situation the cell or entire partition will be reset. The data field contains the return status for the function that encountered the error.

hpevtBootMoveSlavesDispatcherAddrErr.name: hpevtBootMoveSlavesDispatcherAddrErr
hpevtBootMoveSlavesDispatcherAddrErr.description: PDC is about to halt the cell because PDC was unable to determine the GNI address of the SlaveDispatcher function of PDC relocated to memory by PDC. The data field contains the error return value from the function GetGniCodeAddrFromRomCodeAddr().

hpevtBootMoveSlavesCheckSlaveErr.name: hpevtBootMoveSlavesCheckSlaveErr
hpevtBootMoveSlavesCheckSlaveErr.description: PDC is about to halt the cell because at least one of the processors didn't complete the task for which they were awakened and then return to sleep. The data field contains an error return status.

hpevtBootMoveSlavesFpSetAddrErr.name: hpevtBootMoveSlavesFpSetAddrErr
hpevtBootMoveSlavesFpSetAddrErr.description: PDC is about to halt the cell because PDC was unable to determine the GNI address of the CpuFpSet() function of PDC relocated to memory by PDC. The data field contains the error return value from the function GetGniCodeAddrFromRomCodeAddr().

hpevtBootMoveSlavesFpSetErr.name: hpevtBootMoveSlavesFpSetErr
hpevtBootMoveSlavesFpSetErr.description: PDC is about to halt the cell because one or more of the slaves were unable to change their CPU FP state in PDH memory on the local cell. The data field contains an error return status.

hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsStructAddrErr.name: hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsStructAddrErr
hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsStructAddrErr.description: PDC was trying to move the cell monarchs on each of the non-core cells into the Dispatcher, but in order to do that, the PD monarch needs to be able to read the CPU number of the cell monarch on each of the non-core cells, which is kept in a data structure on each of the cells. PDC was unable to get the address to the CELL_CPU_STATE structure in PDH memory in a cell in the partition. The data field is the error return status from the PDC function called PdhGetHCellStructAddr().

hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsCheckSlaveErr.name: hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsCheckSlaveErr
hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsCheckSlaveErr.description: PDC is about to reset the partition because at least one of the processors didn't complete the task for which they were awakened and then return to sleep. The data field contains the error return status from the PDC function CheckSingleSlave().

hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsFpSetAddrErr.name: hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsFpSetAddrErr
hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsFpSetAddrErr.description: PDC is about to reset the partition because it is unable to determine the GNI address for the CpuFpSet() function for one or more of the cells in the partition. The data field contains the error return status from GetGniCodeAddrFromRomCodeAddr().

hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsFpSetErr.name: hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsFpSetErr
hpevtBootMoveCellMonarchsFpSetErr.description: PDC is about to reset the partition because one or more of the processors were unable to successfully modify their CPU FP State (aka their PST state). The data field contains the error return status from the CpuFpSet() function.

hpevtBootDeconfigCpuModulePair.name: hpevtBootDeconfigCpuModulePair
hpevtBootDeconfigCpuModulePair.description: A cpu that is attached to a cpu that is slated for deconfiguration is being deconfigured as well.

hpevtBootVirtualizeDualCoreRegistersFail.name: hpevtBootVirtualizeDualCoreRegistersFail
hpevtBootVirtualizeDualCoreRegistersFail.description: FW failed to virtualize the mx2 interposer.

hpevtBootVirtualizeDualCoreInterposerFai.name: hpevtBootVirtualizeDualCoreInterposerFail
hpevtBootVirtualizeDualCoreInterposerFai.description: FW has failed to virtualize the mx2 interposer.

hpevtBootInstallPmiHandlerFailed.name: hpevtBootInstallPmiHandlerFailed
hpevtBootInstallPmiHandlerFailed.description: Installation of the FW PMI handler has failed.

hpevtPdhcCellIncompatable.name: hpevtPdhcCellIncompatable
hpevtPdhcCellIncompatable.description: Cell and or cpus have failed compatibility checks.

hpevtPdhcPdhNotAvailable.name: hpevtPdhcPdhNotAvailable
hpevtPdhcPdhNotAvailable.description: PDH space not available after release from reset.

hpevtAllCpusDeconfOnCell.name: hpevtAllCpusDeconfOnCell
hpevtAllCpusDeconfOnCell.description: All possible CPUs on a cell have been scheduled for deconfiguration.

hpevtFabricLogRoutingRdErr.name: hpevtFabricLogRoutingRdErr
hpevtFabricLogRoutingRdErr.description: A read error occurred while dumping the XBC port routing registers during boot. This cell will attempt fabricless boot. Data field: (XBC port << 48) | (XBC num << 32) | error status reg

hpevtFabricLinkRendezDisableErr.name: hpevtFabricLinkRendezDisableErr
hpevtFabricLinkRendezDisableErr.description: After cell rendezvous for a 2 cell Medel, only one cell made it into the partition. Disabling the link failed. The cell will reset for reconfig. Data Field: return status

hpevtAcDeletedA0.name: hpevtAcDeletedA0
hpevtAcDeletedA0.description: Power is no longer being supplied to input A0 on the cabinet specified in the data field.

hpevtAcDeletedA1.name: hpevtAcDeletedA1
hpevtAcDeletedA1.description: Power is no longer being supplied to input A1 on the cabinet specified in the data field.

hpevtAcDeletedB0.name: hpevtAcDeletedB0
hpevtAcDeletedB0.description: Power is no longer being supplied to input B0 on the cabinet specified in the data field.

hpevtAcDeletedB1.name: hpevtAcDeletedB1
hpevtAcDeletedB1.description: Power is no longer being supplied to input B1 on the cabinet specified in the data field.

hpevtFabricCc2CcLinkDisableErr.name: hpevtFabricCc2CcLinkDisableErr
hpevtFabricCc2CcLinkDisableErr.description: Failed to disable the XIN link init CSR on a XBCless system. Cell will halt. Data field: return status (0 = SUCCESS, -1 = FAILURE), -1 is expected for this event.

hpevtFabricISREarlyCopyRoutingErr.name: hpevtFabricISREarlyCopyRoutingErr
hpevtFabricISREarlyCopyRoutingErr.description: Error writing the XBC port's routing registers. The cell will reboot. Data Field: XBC port << 44 | XBC num << 32 | return status

hpevtFabricClrLinkInitBitErrMaskRd.name: hpevtFabricClrLinkInitBitErrMaskRd
hpevtFabricClrLinkInitBitErrMaskRd.description: Could not read the XIN error mask register on the CC. Data Field: cell number and return status

hpevtFabricClrLinkInitBitErrMaskWr.name: hpevtFabricClrLinkInitBitErrMaskWr
hpevtFabricClrLinkInitBitErrMaskWr.description: Could not write the XIN error mask register on the CC. Data Field: cell number and return status

hpevtFabricPortPairRdPstatusErr.name: hpevtFabricPortPairRdPstatusErr
hpevtFabricPortPairRdPstatusErr.description: While testing link traversability, a XBC CSR could not be read. Data Field: Port Number << 44 | XBC Number << 32 | return value

hpevtPdhBatteryPowerLow.name: hpevtPdhBatteryPowerLow
hpevtPdhBatteryPowerLow.description: The Battery-Low interrupt was signaled in the Interrupt Pending Register in Dillon (PDH) by the hardware. PDHC is merely reporting the problem.

hpevtNoHandoffToOsMca.name: hpevtNoHandoffToOsMca
hpevtNoHandoffToOsMca.description: This means that the system FW MCA handler is not going to handoff to the OS_MCA handler.

hpevtBootRtnFromSwCantGetCounters.name: hpevtBootRtnFromSwCantGetCounters
hpevtBootRtnFromSwCantGetCounters.description: When returning from other software, like when returning from ISL, PDC is trying to make sure that all of the slave processors in the partition are asleep; however, this event ID indicates that we were unable to access PDH memory of a cell that is supposed to be part of our partition. The data field contains the error return status from a function called SleepAndWakeupCountersGet().

hpevtBootRtnFromSwCpuNotAsleep.name: hpevtBootRtnFromSwCpuNotAsleep
hpevtBootRtnFromSwCpuNotAsleep.description: When returning to PDC from other software, like returning from ISL, PDC tries to verify that all the slave processors are in the expected state (i.e. that all slave processors are asleep); however, this event ID indicates that at least one processor active in the partition was not asleep. So, PDC is going to reset the partition. The data field of this Event ID is the global CPU number of the first CPU in the partition not found in the expected state.

hpevtBootDeconfigAbsentCantSetCpuState.name: hpevtBootDeconfigAbsentCantSetCpuState
hpevtBootDeconfigAbsentCantSetCpuState.description: PDC could not access one of its own data structures on the local cell. The cell will be halted. The data field contains the return status from the PDC function that encountered the error.

hpevtNvramBlockTableCorrupt.name: hpevtNvramBlockTableCorrupt
hpevtNvramBlockTableCorrupt.description: The NVRAM-based descriptor for System Firmware NVRAM blocks is corrupt.

hpevtBootMoveSlavesSetTimeoutErr.name: hpevtBootMoveSlavesSetTimeoutErr
hpevtBootMoveSlavesSetTimeoutErr.description: The cell will be reset because it was unable to access PDH memory on its own cell. While trying to move all the slave processors on the cell to the 'late boot sleep', the monarch tried to write the sleep timeout to PDH memory on its own cell, but encountered an error in doing so. The data field contains a PDC return status.

hpevtBootReconfigAllCpus.name: hpevtBootReconfigAllCpus
hpevtBootReconfigAllCpus.description: All CPUs have been determined to be manually deconfigured in NVM during boot. This may only happen when switching from single core CPU deconfiguration to multi-core CPU deconfiguration in product qualification testing. As a recovery, NVM settings have been changed to reconfigure all CPUs.

hpevtBootGetNumcoresFailure.name: hpevtBootGetNumcoresFailure
hpevtBootGetNumcoresFailure.description: A failure has occurred trying to determine the number of CPU cores per module. Depending upon the situation, either the cell will be halted or the entire partition will be reset.

hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortTopoErr.name: hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortTopoErr
hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortTopoErr.description: While writing the remote routing, the local XBC could not be accessed to determine the topology. Look for additional chassis codes to determine what will happen as a result of this failure. Data field: return status, either SUCCESS (0) or (-1)

hpevtFabricCellRerouteFailure.name: hpevtFabricCellRerouteFailure
hpevtFabricCellRerouteFailure.description: Failed to route around a broken link on cell reboot. Data Field: PDC return status

hpevtFabricRdFailedLinksError.name: hpevtFabricRdFailedLinksError
hpevtFabricRdFailedLinksError.description: Could not read the XBC register that contains the number of links that are currently broken on the complex. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricWrFailedLinksRdError.name: hpevtFabricWrFailedLinksRdError
hpevtFabricWrFailedLinksRdError.description: Could not read the XBC register that contains the number of links that are currently broken on the complex. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricWrFailedLinksWrError.name: hpevtFabricWrFailedLinksWrError
hpevtFabricWrFailedLinksWrError.description: Could not write the XBC register that contains the number of links that are currently broken on the complex. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricIncFailedLinksRdError.name: hpevtFabricIncFailedLinksRdError
hpevtFabricIncFailedLinksRdError.description: Could not read the XBC register that contains the number of links that are currently broken on the complex. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricIncFailedLinksWrError.name: hpevtFabricIncFailedLinksWrError
hpevtFabricIncFailedLinksWrError.description: Could not write the XBC register that contains the number of links that are currently broken on the complex. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricIncFailedLinksHitLimit.name: hpevtFabricIncFailedLinksHitLimit
hpevtFabricIncFailedLinksHitLimit.description: Too many broken crossbar links were found. This cell will have no connectivity to other cells in the complex. It will attempt a fabricless boot, except in a few configurations. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | number of broken links

hpevtFabricRtgCompleteRdFldLinksErr.name: hpevtFabricRtgCompleteRdFldLinksErr
hpevtFabricRtgCompleteRdFldLinksErr.description: Could not read the XBC register that contains the number of links that are currently broken on the complex. Data Field: PDC return status

hpevtFabricRtgCompleteWrFldLinksErr.name: hpevtFabricRtgCompleteWrFldLinksErr
hpevtFabricRtgCompleteWrFldLinksErr.description: Could not write the XBC register that contains the number of links that are currently broken on the complex. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricCellRerouteRdXbcErr.name: hpevtFabricCellRerouteRdXbcErr
hpevtFabricCellRerouteRdXbcErr.description: Could not read the XBC register that marks the ports that have been routed around. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricCellRerouteNbrNotReachable.name: hpevtFabricCellRerouteNbrNotReachable
hpevtFabricCellRerouteNbrNotReachable.description: The PIOB route to the remote XBC was not traversable. The cell will halt. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricCellRerouteSm4RlsErr.name: hpevtFabricCellRerouteSm4RlsErr
hpevtFabricCellRerouteSm4RlsErr.description: Could not release the remote XBC's semaphore. Cell will halt. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortBcastWrErr.name: hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortBcastWrErr
hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortBcastWrErr.description: Failed to complete a broadcast write to an XBC. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortRdErr.name: hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortRdErr
hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortRdErr.description: Failed to complete a read to the built-in port of a XBC. Data Field: (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortWrErr.name: hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortWrErr
hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortWrErr.description: Failed to complete a write to the local cell's port of the XBC. Data Field: (XBC Port << 44) | (XBC Num << 32) | PDC return status

hpevtIoLinkSubsystemFailed.name: hpevtIoLinkSubsystemFailed
hpevtIoLinkSubsystemFailed.description: The link between the CC and SBA failed meaning that I/O is not available to the reporting cell.

hpevtIoSbaSubsystemFailed.name: hpevtIoSbaSubsystemFailed
hpevtIoSbaSubsystemFailed.description: An error was detected in the SBA and the reporting cell has no I/O.

hpevtIoErrengineError.name: hpevtIoErrengineError
hpevtIoErrengineError.description: The structured exception handling within the system firmware failed during I/O initialization.

hpevtIoDiscEeMallocErr.name: hpevtIoDiscEeMallocErr
hpevtIoDiscEeMallocErr.description: There is not enough malloc resources for the I/O structure exception handling. I/O on the reported cell is not available.

hpevtIoDiscEeCreatetreeErr.name: hpevtIoDiscEeCreatetreeErr
hpevtIoDiscEeCreatetreeErr.description: Error creating the structure for housing the I/O structured exception handling services and data. I/O is lost on the reporting cell.

hpevtIoDiscEeAttachserviceErr.name: hpevtIoDiscEeAttachserviceErr
hpevtIoDiscEeAttachserviceErr.description: Unable to bind the I/O structure exception handling to the internal data structures.

hpevtIoDiscEeInitErr.name: hpevtIoDiscEeInitErr
hpevtIoDiscEeInitErr.description: Error detected while initializing the I/O structure exception handling services.

hpevtIoDiscEeInitializationErr.name: hpevtIoDiscEeInitializationErr
hpevtIoDiscEeInitializationErr.description: Error initializing the I/O structure exception handling data structures.

hpevtIoDiscEeContextErr.name: hpevtIoDiscEeContextErr
hpevtIoDiscEeContextErr.description: The structured I/O exception handling data structures have an error. All I/O on the reporting cell is not available.

hpevtIoDiscCreateSbaNodeErr.name: hpevtIoDiscCreateSbaNodeErr
hpevtIoDiscCreateSbaNodeErr.description: While setting up the internal SBA data and service an error was detected. All I/O for the reporting cell is not available.

hpevtIoDiscSbaAttachserviceErr.name: hpevtIoDiscSbaAttachserviceErr
hpevtIoDiscSbaAttachserviceErr.description: An error attaching firmware services to the internal structures was detected. All I/O on the reporting cell is not available.

hpevtIoDiscSbaInitnodeErr.name: hpevtIoDiscSbaInitnodeErr
hpevtIoDiscSbaInitnodeErr.description: System firmware detected an error initializing internal SBA data structures and services. This is usually an error with unavailable resources.

hpevtIoDiscSbaUnknownErr.name: hpevtIoDiscSbaUnknownErr
hpevtIoDiscSbaUnknownErr.description: The SBA type is unknown to the system firmware. The I/O on the reporting cell is not available.

hpevtIoDeviceMissing.name: hpevtIoDeviceMissing
hpevtIoDeviceMissing.description: An expected I/O device cannot be detected by the system firmware.

hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortBadReroute.name: hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortBadReroute
hpevtFabricRmtRoutePortBadReroute.description: Too many broken links! The XBC port route around failed because the route-around port was bad too. Data field: (XBC port << 44) | (XBC num << 32) | port state

hpevtAgtPredictMemFail.name: hpevtAgtPredictMemFail
hpevtAgtPredictMemFail.description: ECC (Error Checking and Correcting) memory is designed to detect and correct single-bit errors that occasionally occur in computer systems. This memory module is currently correcting many single bit errors.

hpevtWinAgtLockedProperty.name: hpevtWinAgtLockedProperty
hpevtWinAgtLockedProperty.description: Server Agents SNMP branch is not responding due to a portion of the IPMI Management Subsystem being locked by another entity.

hpevtIoPciPowerOverloadErr.name: hpevtIoPciPowerOverloadErr
hpevtIoPciPowerOverloadErr.description: A non-hot plug I/O slot's power consumption increases the total I/O power consumption beyond the supported limit. Firmware will display the following EFI error message, 'I/O configuration exceeds power limit' and disallow O/S boot. Data Field: Physical location of the I/O slot.

hpevtMemSbeSeedingEnabled.name: hpevtMemSbeSeedingEnabled
hpevtMemSbeSeedingEnabled.description: This is a warning that the system is running in a degraded mode. It will only be emitted in MFG mode when Memory SBE Seeding is enabled. This is only for testing of SBE seeding for LAB and possibly MFG use ONLY. It should NEVER be seen in the field.

hpevtFabricWrFailedLinksTopoErr.name: hpevtFabricWrFailedLinksTopoErr
hpevtFabricWrFailedLinksTopoErr.description: Read failure while writing the number of failed links to the XBC. Data Field: Return Status (SUCCESS = 0, FAILURE = -1)

hpevtBootErrInitGroupCPaFields.name: hpevtBootErrInitGroupCPaFields
hpevtBootErrInitGroupCPaFields.description: PDC could not access a complex profile. The partition will be reset because the available complex profile is not valid. Data field contains the return status from the function that encountered the error.

hpevtFabricAssertFabricHop.name: hpevtFabricAssertFabricHop
hpevtFabricAssertFabricHop.description: An unexpected error occurred while initializing the fabric. The firmware is not able to analyze this error. Clues to the cause of this error may be found in the IPMI forward progress log (FPL) either shortly before or after this log entry occurred. The FPL is available from the management processor using the 'sl' command. HP-UX also saves these logs in the /var/stm/logs/os directory, and they can be viewed using the slview utility.

hpevtBootFailedReadingProfileCInIcm.name: hpevtBootFailedReadingProfileCInIcm
hpevtBootFailedReadingProfileCInIcm.description: PDC could not access a complex profile. The partition will be reset. Data field contains the return status from the function that encountered the error.

hpevtFabricHaltLinkDisableErr.name: hpevtFabricHaltLinkDisableErr
hpevtFabricHaltLinkDisableErr.description: Before attempting a fabricless boot, the cell's link to the fabric should be disabled to provide isolation and stability. The link could not be disabled, so the cell will halt.

hpevtBootGetSpiromGetSiblingErr.name: hpevtBootGetSpiromGetSiblingErr
hpevtBootGetSpiromGetSiblingErr.description: Configuration information on the processor was invalid. The cell will be halted. Data field contains the return value from the function that encountered the error.

hpevtCpuClockRatioMismatch.name: hpevtCpuClockRatioMismatch
hpevtCpuClockRatioMismatch.description: The clock ratio that the processor is running at does not match the clock ratio that manageability is reporting.

hpevtBootStopBootOverride.name: hpevtBootStopBootOverride
hpevtBootStopBootOverride.description: The user has manually bypassed a stop boot condition (caused by an error during boot) and continued to boot an O/S. The system might experience unpredictable failures.

hpevtVgaBiosRelocFail.name: hpevtVgaBiosRelocFail
hpevtVgaBiosRelocFail.description: Firmware was unable to relocate the VGA BIOS to the hardcoded VGA BIOS region in main memory (physical address range 0xc0000 - 0xdffff). VGA routing has been disabled by firmware. No VGA device will be accessible on this boot.

hpevtCompMatrixXsumError.name: hpevtCompMatrixXsumError
hpevtCompMatrixXsumError.description: The component compatibility matrix stored in NVRAM and used by system firmware has a checksum error. The stored value does not equal the calculated value. The data field will contain first the expected value, and the subsequent code will contain the actual data.

hpevtBootGetDefaultRdrsFailed.name: hpevtBootGetDefaultRdrsFailed
hpevtBootGetDefaultRdrsFailed.description: PDC could not read an internal CPU register. The partition will be reset. Data field is the return status from the function that encountered the error.

hpevtBootGetCurrentRdrsFailed.name: hpevtBootGetCurrentRdrsFailed
hpevtBootGetCurrentRdrsFailed.description: PDC could not read an internal CPU register. The partition will be reset. Data field is the return status from the function that encountered the error.

hpevtBootReadPrefetchFailed.name: hpevtBootReadPrefetchFailed
hpevtBootReadPrefetchFailed.description: PDC failed reading a value out of its own copy of the internal CPU register settings. Data field is a status return indicating the type of failure.

hpevtBootReadZlcoFailed.name: hpevtBootReadZlcoFailed
hpevtBootReadZlcoFailed.description: PDC failed reading a value out of its own copy of the internal CPU register settings. Data field is a status return indicating the type of failure.

hpevtBootUpdateZlcoAndPrefetchFailed.name: hpevtBootUpdateZlcoAndPrefetchFailed
hpevtBootUpdateZlcoAndPrefetchFailed.description: PDC attempted to update CPU registers to match their respective settings in the complex profile, but a failure was returned from the call to accomplish the update. Data field contains the failure.

hpevtBootErrorReadingZlcoFlagInPdProfile.name: hpevtBootErrorReadingZlcoFlagInPdProfile
hpevtBootErrorReadingZlcoFlagInPdProfile.description: PDC could not access a complex profile. The partition will be reset.. Data field contains the return status from the function that encountered the error.

hpevtBootFindCoreCellCmplxProfileAcErr.name: hpevtBootFindCoreCellCmplxProfileAcErr
hpevtBootFindCoreCellCmplxProfileAcErr.description: PDC could not access a complex profile. The cell will be reset. Data field contains the return status from the function that encountered the error.

hpevtBootFindCoreCellConfigSelectErr.name: hpevtBootFindCoreCellConfigSelectErr
hpevtBootFindCoreCellConfigSelectErr.description: Could not find a potential core cell for the partition in the configured set. This cell will reset for reconfiguration. Data Field: return status from failing function

hpevtBootCellLclCantFindViable.name: hpevtBootCellLclCantFindViable
hpevtBootCellLclCantFindViable.description: The potential core cell was not viable (i.e. no core I/O, etc). This cell will reset for reconfiguration. Data Field: bit mask of cells that made the rendezvous set

hpevtBootCellRmtCantFindViable.name: hpevtBootCellRmtCantFindViable
hpevtBootCellRmtCantFindViable.description: The potential core cell was not viable (i.e. no core I/O, etc). This cell will reset for reconfiguration. Data Field: bit mask of cells that made the rendezvous set

hpevtBootFindCoreCellNotInRendez.name: hpevtBootFindCoreCellNotInRendez
hpevtBootFindCoreCellNotInRendez.description: The potential core cell did not rendezvous with the rest of the partition. This cell cannot talk to the selected core cell. This cell will reset for reconfiguration. Data Field: bit mask of cells that made the rendezvous set

hpevtBootFindCoreCellLclNotViable.name: hpevtBootFindCoreCellLclNotViable
hpevtBootFindCoreCellLclNotViable.description: The local cell is disconnected from the rest of the system due to the main backplane configuration. While the partition is only configured to contain a single cell, the local cell is not a viable core cell. The cell will reset for reconfiguration. Data Field: bit mask of cells that made the rendezvous set

hpevtBootFindCoreCellFabriclessPdErr.name: hpevtBootFindCoreCellFabriclessPdErr
hpevtBootFindCoreCellFabriclessPdErr.description: This cell has booted without the main backplane, probably due to prior main backplane errors. The partition it is in is configured with 3 or more cells. The combination of these two configurations is not allowed. The cell will reset for reconfiguration. Data Field: configured set

hpevtRtcAccessError.name: hpevtRtcAccessError
hpevtRtcAccessError.description: While validating the internal RTC data the data is read twice and compared. If the comparison fails to match the read is performed again up a maximum of 50 times. If we cannot get a match in 50 retries we issue this event.

hpevtBootAccessCellArchErr.name: hpevtBootAccessCellArchErr
hpevtBootAccessCellArchErr.description: PDC attempts to make sure that all of the cells in a partition are installed in the same processor architecture. PDC failed to read the architecture for another cell. PDC will reset all of the cells in the partition when this error is detected. The data field contains the physical location of the cell reporting the event.

hpevtXbcLogSizeErr.name: hpevtXbcLogSizeErr
hpevtXbcLogSizeErr.description: The buffer size passed in to the XBC error logging routine through SAL_GET_STATE_INFO, SAL_CLEAR_STATE_INFO, or MCA logging is too small for the XBC error log Data field consists of: XBC number (32:43)

hpevtXbcLogClearErr.name: hpevtXbcLogClearErr
hpevtXbcLogClearErr.description: System firmware was unable to clear an XBC error. The data field contains: XBC number (32:43) port number (44:55) error type (0:31)

hpevtIodiscPciLogError.name: hpevtIodiscPciLogError
hpevtIodiscPciLogError.description: Error encountered while collecting PCI error logs. The result is some or all PCI error logs will be unavailable.

hpevtIodiscSbaLogError.name: hpevtIodiscSbaLogError
hpevtIodiscSbaLogError.description: Error encountered while collecting SBA error logs. The result is some or all SBA error logs will be unavailable.

hpevtXbcInitMaxRetries.name: hpevtXbcInitMaxRetries
